  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: f0e13320f8bc1254f8bca32b62d9305b, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Requests Wisdom'
      title: Solomon Requests Wisdom
      number: 1
      content: Now Solomon the son of David was strengthened in his kingdom, and
        the Lord his God was with him and exalted him exceedingly.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Solomon spoke to all Israel, to the captains of thousands and
        of hundreds, to the judges, and to every leader in all Israel, the heads
        of the fathers\u2019 houses.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Solomon, and all the assembly with him, went to the high place
        that was at Gibeon; for the tabernacle of meeting with God was there, which
        Moses the servant of the Lord had made in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But David had brought up the ark of God from Kirjath Jearim to the 
        place David had prepared for it, for he had pitched a tent for it at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the bronze altar that Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur,
        had made, he put before the tabernacle of the Lord; Solomon and the assembly
        sought Him there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And Solomon went up there to the bronze altar before the Lord, which
        was at the tabernacle of meeting, and offered a thousand burnt offerings
        on it.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "On that night God appeared to Solomon, and said to him, \u201CAsk!
        What shall I give you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Solomon said to God: \u201CYou have shown great mercy to David
        my father, and have made me king in his place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Now, O Lord God, let Your promise to David my father be established,
        for You have made me king over a people like the dust of the earth in multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now give me wisdom and knowledge, that I may go out and come in before
        this people; for who can judge this great people of Yours?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then God said to Solomon: \u201CBecause this was in your heart, and
        you have not asked riches or wealth or honor or the life of your enemies,
        nor have you asked long life\u2014but have asked wisdom and knowledge for
        yourself, that you may judge My people over whom I have made you king\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Solomon\u2019s Military and Economic Power"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Military and Economic Power"
      number: 12
      content: "wisdom and knowledge are granted to you; and I will give you riches
        and wealth and honor, such as none of the kings have had who were before
        you, nor shall any after you have the like.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Solomon came to Jerusalem from the high place that was at Gibeon,
        from before the tabernacle of meeting, and reigned over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And Solomon gathered chariots and horsemen; he had one thousand four
        hundred chariots and twelve thousand horsemen, whom he stationed in the chariot
        cities and with the king in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Also the king made silver and gold as common in Jerusalem as stones,
        and he made cedars as abundant as the sycamores which are in the lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And Solomon had horses imported from Egypt and Keveh; the king\u2019s
        merchants bought them in Keveh at the current price. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: They also acquired and imported from Egypt a chariot for six hundred
        shekels of silver, and a horse for one hundred and fifty; thus, through their
        agents, they exported them to all the kings of the Hittites and the kings
        of Syria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Prepares to Build the Temple'
      title: Solomon Prepares to Build the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Solomon determined to build a temple for the name of the Lord,
        and a royal house for himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: Solomon selected seventy thousand men to bear burdens, eighty thousand
        to quarry stone in the mountains, and three thousand six hundred to oversee
        them.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Solomon sent to Hiram king of Tyre, saying:As you have dealt
        with David my father, and sent him cedars to build himself a house to dwell
        in, so  deal  with  me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Behold, I am building a temple for the name of the Lord my God, to
        dedicate it to Him, to burn before Him sweet incense, for the continual showbread,
        for the burnt offerings morning and evening, on the Sabbaths, on the New
        Moons, and on the set feasts of the Lord our God. This is  an  ordinance
        forever to Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the temple which I build will  be great, for our God is greater
        than all gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: But who is able to build Him a temple, since heaven and the heaven
        of heavens cannot contain Him? Who am I then, that I should build Him a temple,
        except to burn sacrifice before Him?
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore send me at once a man skillful to work in gold and silver,
        in bronze and iron, in purple and crimson and blue, who has skill to engrave
        with the skillful men who are with me in Judah and Jerusalem, whom David
        my father provided. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Also send me cedar and cypress and algum logs from Lebanon, for I
        know that your servants have skill to cut timber in Lebanon; and indeed my
        servants will  be with your servants, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: to prepare timber for me in abundance, for the temple which I am about
        to build shall  be great and wonderful.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And indeed I will give to your servants, the woodsmen who cut timber,
        twenty thousand kors of ground wheat, twenty thousand kors of barley, twenty
        thousand baths of wine, and twenty thousand baths of oil.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then Hiram king of Tyre answered in writing, which he sent to Solomon:Because
        the Lord loves His people, He has made you king over them.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Hiram also said:Blessed be the Lord God of Israel, who made heaven
        and earth, for He has given King David a wise son, endowed with prudence
        and understanding, who will build a temple for the Lord and a royal house
        for himself!
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: And now I have sent a skillful man, endowed with understanding, Huram
        my master craftsman
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: (the son of a woman of the daughters of Dan, and his father was a
        man of Tyre), skilled to work in gold and silver, bronze and iron, stone
        and wood, purple and blue, fine linen and crimson, and to make any engraving
        and to accomplish any plan which may be given to him, with your skillful
        men and with the skillful men of my lord David your father.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Now therefore, the wheat, the barley, the oil, and the wine which
        my lord has spoken of, let him send to his servants.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And we will cut wood from Lebanon, as much as you need; we will bring
        it to you in rafts by sea to Joppa, and you will carry it up to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Solomon numbered all the aliens who were in the land of Israel,
        after the census in which David his father had numbered them; and there were
        found to be one hundred and fifty-three thousand six hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And he made seventy thousand of them bearers of burdens, eighty thousand
        stonecutters in the mountain, and three thousand six hundred overseers to
        make the people work.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Builds the Temple'
      title: Solomon Builds the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Solomon began to build the house of the Lord at Jerusalem on
        Mount Moriah, where the  Lord had appeared to his father David, at the place
        that David had prepared on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And he began to build on the second day of the second month in the
        fourth year of his reign.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'This is the foundation which Solomon laid for building the house
        of God: The length was sixty cubits (by cubits according to the former measure)
        and the width twenty cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the vestibule that was in front of the sanctuary was twenty cubits
        long across the width of the house, and the height was one hundred and twenty.
        He overlaid the inside with pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The larger room he paneled with cypress which he overlaid with fine
        gold, and he carved palm trees and chainwork on it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he decorated the house with precious stones for beauty, and the
        gold was gold from Parvaim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He also overlaid the house\u2014the beams and doorposts, its walls
        and doors\u2014with gold; and he carved cherubim on the walls."
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he made the Most Holy Place. Its length was according to the
        width of the house, twenty cubits, and its width twenty cubits. He overlaid
        it with six hundred talents of fine gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The weight of the nails was fifty shekels of gold; and he overlaid
        the upper area with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In the Most Holy Place he made two cherubim, fashioned by carving,
        and overlaid them with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The wings of the cherubim were twenty cubits in overall length: one
        wing of  the  one  cherub  was five cubits, touching the wall of the room,
        and the other wing was five cubits, touching the wing of the other cherub; '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'one wing of the other cherub was five cubits, touching the wall of
        the room, and the other wing also  was five cubits, touching the wing of
        the other cherub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The wings of these cherubim spanned twenty cubits overall. They stood
        on their feet, and they faced inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And he made the veil of blue, purple, crimson, and fine linen, and
        wove cherubim into it.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Also he made in front of the temple two pillars thirty-five cubits
        high, and the capital that was on the top of each of them was five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He made wreaths of chainwork, as in the inner sanctuary, and put
        them on top of the pillars; and he made one hundred pomegranates, and put
        them on the wreaths of chainwork. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Then he set up the pillars before the temple, one on the right hand
        and the other on the left; he called the name of the one on the right hand
        Jachin, and the name of the one on the left Boaz.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Furnishings of the Temple'
      title: Furnishings of the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'Moreover he made a bronze altar: twenty cubits was its length, twenty
        cubits its width, and ten cubits its height.'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he made the Sea of cast bronze, ten cubits from one brim to
        the other; it  was completely round. Its height was five cubits, and a line
        of thirty cubits measured its circumference. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And under it was the likeness of oxen encircling it all around, ten
        to a cubit, all the way around the Sea. The oxen were cast in two rows, when
        it was cast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'It stood on twelve oxen: three looking toward the north, three looking
        toward the west, three looking toward the south, and three looking toward
        the east; the Sea was  set upon them, and all their back parts pointed inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: It was a handbreadth thick; and its brim was shaped like the brim
        of a cup, like a lily blossom. It contained three thousand baths.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He also made ten lavers, and put five on the right side and five
        on the left, to wash in them; such things as they offered for the burnt offering
        they would wash in them, but the Sea was for the priests to wash in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he made ten lampstands of gold according to their design, and
        set them in the temple, five on the right side and five on the left. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: He also made ten tables, and placed them in the temple, five on the
        right side and five on the left. And he made one hundred bowls of gold.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Furthermore he made the court of the priests, and the great court
        and doors for the court; and he overlaid these doors with bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: He set the Sea on the right side, toward the southeast.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Huram made the pots and the shovels and the bowls. So Huram
        finished doing the work that he was to do for King Solomon for the house
        of God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'the two pillars and the bowl-shaped capitals that  were on top of
        the two pillars; the two networks covering the two bowl-shaped capitals which
        were on top of the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'four hundred pomegranates for the two networks (two rows of pomegranates
        for each network, to cover the two bowl-shaped capitals that were on the
        pillars); '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'he also made carts and the lavers on the carts; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'one Sea and twelve oxen under it; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "also the pots, the shovels, the forks\u2014and all their articles
        Huram his master craftsman made of burnished bronze for King Solomon for
        the house of the Lord."
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'In the plain of Jordan the king had them cast in clay molds, between
        Succoth and Zeredah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And Solomon had all these articles made in such great abundance that
        the weight of the bronze was not determined.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Thus Solomon had all the furnishings made for the house of God: the
        altar of gold and the tables on which was  the showbread; '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'the lampstands with their lamps of pure gold, to burn in the prescribed
        manner in front of the inner sanctuary, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'with the flowers and the lamps and the wick-trimmers of gold, of
        purest gold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: the trimmers, the bowls, the ladles, and the censers of pure gold.
        As for the entry of the sanctuary, its inner doors to the Most Holy Place,
        and the doors of the main hall of the temple, were gold.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Brought into the Temple'
      title: The Ark Brought into the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'So all the work that Solomon had done for the house of the Lord was
        finished; and Solomon brought in the things which his father David had dedicated:
        the silver and the gold and all the furnishings. And he put them in the treasuries
        of the house of God.'
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of the
        tribes, the chief fathers of the children of Israel, in Jerusalem, that they
        might bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord up from the City of David,
        which is Zion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore all the men of Israel assembled with the king at the feast,
        which was in the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So all the elders of Israel came, and the Levites took up the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then they brought up the ark, the tabernacle of meeting, and all
        the holy furnishings that were in the tabernacle. The priests and the Levites
        brought them up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Also King Solomon, and all the congregation of Israel who were assembled
        with him before the ark, were sacrificing sheep and oxen that could not be
        counted or numbered for multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then the priests brought in the ark of the covenant of the Lord to
        its place, into the inner sanctuary of the temple, to the Most Holy Place,
        under the wings of the cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the cherubim spread their wings over the place of the ark, and
        the cherubim overshadowed the ark and its poles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The poles extended so that the ends of the poles of the ark could
        be seen from the  holy  place, in front of the inner sanctuary; but they
        could not be seen from outside. And they are there to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Nothing was in the ark except the two tablets which Moses put there
        at Horeb, when the Lord made a  covenant with the children of Israel, when
        they had come out of Egypt.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And it came to pass when the priests came out of the Most Holy Place
        (for all the priests who were present had sanctified themselves, without
        keeping to their divisions), '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "and the Levites who  were the singers, all those of Asaph and Heman
        and Jeduthun, with their sons and their brethren, stood at the east end of
        the altar, clothed in white linen, having cymbals, stringed instruments and
        harps, and with them one hundred and twenty priests sounding with trumpets\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "indeed it came to pass, when the trumpeters and singers were as one,
        to make one sound to be heard in praising and thanking the Lord, and when
        they lifted up their voice with the trumpets and cymbals and instruments
        of music, and praised the Lord, saying:\u201CFor He is good,For His mercy
        endures forever,\u201Dthat the house, the house of the Lord, was filled with
        a cloud, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: so that the priests could not continue ministering because of the
        cloud; for the glory of the Lord filled the house of God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: "Then Solomon spoke:\u201CThe Lord said He would dwell in the dark
        cloud."
      comments: []
    - name: "2: Solomon\u2019s Speech upon Completion of the Work"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Speech upon Completion of the Work"
      number: 2
      content: "I have surely built You an exalted house,And a place for You to dwell
        in forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the king turned around and blessed the whole assembly of Israel,
        while all the assembly of Israel was standing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said: \u201CBlessed be the Lord God of Israel, who has fulfilled
        with His hands what He spoke with His mouth to my father David, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u2018Since the day that I brought My people out of the land of Egypt,
        I have chosen no city from any tribe of Israel in  which to build a house,
        that My name might be there, nor did I choose any man to be a ruler over
        My people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Yet I have chosen Jerusalem, that My name may be there, and I have
        chosen David to be over My people Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now it was in the heart of my father David to build a temple for
        the name of the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But the Lord said to my father David, \u2018Whereas it was in your
        heart to build a temple for My name, you did well in that it was in your
        heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Nevertheless you shall not build the temple, but your son who will
        come from your body, he shall build the temple for My name.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the Lord has fulfilled His word which He spoke, and I have filled
        the position of my father David, and sit on the throne of Israel, as the
        Lord promised; and I have built the temple for the name of the Lord God of
        Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Solomon\u2019s Prayer of Dedication"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Prayer of Dedication"
      number: 11
      content: "And there I have put the ark, in which is the covenant of the Lord
        which He made with the children of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Solomon stood before the altar of the Lord in the presence of
        all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: '(for Solomon had made a bronze platform five cubits long, five cubits
        wide, and three cubits high, and had set it in the midst of the court; and
        he stood on it, knelt down on his knees before all the assembly of Israel,
        and spread out his hands toward heaven); '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and he said: \u201CLord God of Israel, there  is no God in heaven
        or on earth like You, who keep Your  covenant and mercy with Your servants
        who walk before You with all their hearts. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You have kept what You promised Your servant David my father; You
        have both spoken with Your mouth and fulfilled it with Your hand, as it 
        is this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore, Lord God of Israel, now keep what You promised Your servant
        David my father, saying, \u2018You shall not fail to have a man sit before
        Me on the throne of Israel, only if your sons take heed to their way, that
        they walk in My law as you have walked before Me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: And now, O Lord God of Israel, let Your word come true, which You
        have spoken to Your servant David.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CBut will God indeed dwell with men on the earth? Behold, heaven
        and the heaven of heavens cannot contain You. How much less this temple which
        I have built! "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Yet regard the prayer of Your servant and his supplication, O Lord
        my God, and listen to the cry and the prayer which Your servant is praying
        before You: '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'that Your eyes may be open toward this temple day and night, toward
        the place where You said You  would put Your name, that You may hear the
        prayer which Your servant makes toward this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And may You hear the supplications of Your servant and of Your people
        Israel, when they pray toward this place. Hear from heaven Your dwelling
        place, and when You hear, forgive.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CIf anyone sins against his neighbor, and is forced to take
        an oath, and comes and takes an oath before Your altar in this temple, "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: then hear from heaven, and act, and judge Your servants, bringing
        retribution on the wicked by bringing his way on his own head, and justifying
        the righteous by giving him according to his righteousness.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201COr if Your people Israel are defeated before an enemy because
        they have sinned against You, and return and confess Your name, and pray
        and make supplication before You in this temple, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of Your people Israel, and
        bring them back to the land which You gave to them and their fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "\u201CWhen the heavens are shut up and there is no rain because they
        have sinned against You, when they pray toward this place and confess Your
        name, and turn from their sin because You afflict them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of Your servants, Your people
        Israel, that You may teach them the good way in which they should walk; and
        send rain on Your land which You have given to Your people as an inheritance.
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CWhen there is famine in the land, pestilence or blight or mildew,
        locusts or grasshoppers; when their enemies besiege them in the land of their
        cities; whatever plague or whatever sickness there  is;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'whatever prayer, whatever supplication is made by anyone, or by all
        Your people Israel, when each one knows his own burden and his own grief,
        and spreads out his hands to this temple: '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'then hear from heaven Your dwelling place, and forgive, and give
        to everyone according to all his ways, whose heart You know (for You alone
        know the hearts of the sons of men), '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: that they may fear You, to walk in Your ways as long as they live
        in the land which You gave to our fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "\u201CMoreover, concerning a foreigner, who is not of Your people
        Israel, but has come from a far country for the sake of Your great name and
        Your mighty hand and Your outstretched arm, when they come and pray in this
        temple; "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: then hear from heaven Your dwelling place, and do according to all
        for which the foreigner calls to You, that all peoples of the earth may know
        Your name and fear You, as do Your people Israel, and that they may know
        that this temple which I have built is called by Your name.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "\u201CWhen Your people go out to battle against their enemies, wherever
        You send them, and when they pray to You toward this city which You have
        chosen and the temple which I have built for Your name, "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: then hear from heaven their prayer and their supplication, and maintain
        their cause.
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "\u201CWhen they sin against You (for there  is  no one who does not
        sin), and You become angry with them and deliver them to the enemy, and they
        take them captive to a land far or near; "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "yet when they come to themselves in the land where they were carried
        captive, and repent, and make supplication to You in the land of their captivity,
        saying, \u2018We have sinned, we have done wrong, and have committed wickedness\u2019; "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'and when they return to You with all their heart and with all their
        soul in the land of their captivity, where they have been carried captive,
        and pray toward their land which You gave to their fathers, the city which
        You have chosen, and toward the temple which I have built for Your name: '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then hear from heaven Your dwelling place their prayer and their
        supplications, and maintain their cause, and forgive Your people who have
        sinned against You. '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: Now, my God, I pray, let Your eyes be open and let Your ears be attentive
        to the prayer made in this place.
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CNow therefore,Arise, O Lord God, to Your resting place,You
        and the ark of Your strength.Let Your priests, O Lord God, be clothed with
        salvation,And let Your saints rejoice in goodness."
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "\u201CO Lord God, do not turn away the face of Your Anointed;Remember
        the mercies of Your servant David.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Dedicates the Temple'
      title: Solomon Dedicates the Temple
      number: 1
      content: 'When Solomon had finished praying, fire came down from heaven and
        consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices; and the glory of the Lord
        filled the temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the priests could not enter the house of the Lord, because the
        glory of the Lord had filled the Lord\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "When all the children of Israel saw how the fire came down, and the
        glory of the Lord on the temple, they bowed their faces to the ground on
        the pavement, and worshiped and praised the Lord, saying:\u201CFor He  is
        good,For His mercy endures forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the king and all the people offered sacrifices before the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'King Solomon offered a sacrifice of twenty-two thousand bulls and
        one hundred and twenty thousand sheep. So the king and all the people dedicated
        the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the priests attended to their services; the Levites also with
        instruments of the music of the Lord, which King David had made to praise
        the Lord, saying, \u201CFor His mercy endures forever,\u201D whenever David
        offered praise by their ministry. The priests sounded trumpets opposite them,
        while all Israel stood."
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Furthermore Solomon consecrated the middle of the court that was in
        front of the house of the Lord; for there he offered burnt offerings and
        the fat of the peace offerings, because the bronze altar which Solomon had
        made was not able to receive the burnt offerings, the grain offerings, and
        the fat.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'At that time Solomon kept the feast seven days, and all Israel with
        him, a very great assembly from the entrance of Hamath to the Brook of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And on the eighth day they held a sacred assembly, for they observed
        the dedication of the altar seven days, and the feast seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'On the twenty-third day of the seventh month he sent the people away
        to their tents, joyful and glad of heart for the good that the Lord had done
        for David, for Solomon, and for His people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: God\u2019s Second Appearance to Solomon"
      title: "God\u2019s Second Appearance to Solomon"
      number: 11
      content: "Thus Solomon finished the house of the Lord and the king\u2019s house;
        and Solomon successfully accomplished all that came into his heart to make
        in the house of the Lord and in his own house."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the Lord  appeared to Solomon by night, and said to him: \u201CI
        have heard your prayer, and have chosen this place for Myself as a house
        of sacrifice. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'When I shut up heaven and there is no rain, or command the locusts
        to devour the land, or send pestilence among My people, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'if My people who are called by My name will humble themselves, and
        pray and seek My face, and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear
        from heaven, and will forgive their sin and heal their land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Now My eyes will be open and My ears attentive to prayer made in
        this place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For now I have chosen and sanctified this house, that My name may
        be there forever; and My eyes and My heart will be there perpetually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As for you, if you walk before Me as your father David walked, and
        do according to all that I have commanded you, and if you keep My statutes
        and My judgments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "then I will establish the throne of your kingdom, as I covenanted
        with David your father, saying, \u2018You shall not fail to  have a man as
        ruler in Israel.\u2019"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CBut if you turn away and forsake My statutes and My commandments
        which I have set before you, and go and serve other gods, and worship them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: then I will uproot them from My land which I have given them; and
        this house which I have sanctified for My name I will cast out of My sight,
        and will make it a proverb and a byword among all peoples.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAnd as  for  this house, which is exalted, everyone who passes
        by it will be astonished and say, \u2018Why has the Lord done thus to this
        land and this house?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then they will answer, \u2018Because they forsook the Lord God of
        their fathers, who brought them out of the land of Egypt, and embraced other
        gods, and worshiped them and served them; therefore He has brought all this
        calamity on them.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Additional Achievements"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Additional Achievements"
      number: 1
      content: 'It came to pass at the end of twenty years, when Solomon had built
        the house of the Lord and his own house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'that the cities which Hiram had given to Solomon, Solomon built them;
        and he settled the children of Israel there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Solomon went to Hamath Zobah and seized it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He also built Tadmor in the wilderness, and all the storage cities
        which he built in Hamath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He built Upper Beth Horon and Lower Beth Horon, fortified cities
        with walls, gates, and bars, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: also Baalath and all the storage cities that Solomon had, and all
        the chariot cities and the cities of the cavalry, and all that Solomon desired
        to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All the people who  were left of the Hittites, Amorites, Perizzites,
        Hivites, and Jebusites, who were not of Israel\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "that is, their descendants who were left in the land after them,
        whom the children of Israel did not destroy\u2014from these Solomon raised
        forced labor, as it is to this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But Solomon did not make the children of Israel servants for his
        work. Some were men of war, captains of his officers, captains of his chariots,
        and his cavalry. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And others were chiefs of the officials of King Solomon: two hundred
        and fifty, who ruled over the people.'
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now Solomon brought the daughter of Pharaoh up from the City of David
        to the house he had built for her, for he said, \u201CMy wife shall not dwell
        in the house of David king of Israel, because the  places to which the ark
        of the Lord has come are holy.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then Solomon offered burnt offerings to the Lord on the altar of
        the Lord which he had built before the vestibule, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "according to the daily rate, offering according to the commandment
        of Moses, for the Sabbaths, the New Moons, and the three appointed yearly
        feasts\u2014the Feast of Unleavened Bread, the Feast of Weeks, and the Feast
        of Tabernacles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And, according to the order of David his father, he appointed the
        divisions of the priests for their service, the Levites for their duties
        (to praise and serve before the priests) as the duty of each day required,
        and the gatekeepers by their divisions at each gate; for so David the man
        of God had commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They did not depart from the command of the king to the priests and
        Levites concerning any matter or concerning the treasuries.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Now all the work of Solomon was well-ordered from the day of the foundation
        of the house of the Lord until it was finished. So the house of the Lord
        was completed.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Solomon went to Ezion Geber and Elath on the seacoast, in the
        land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And Hiram sent him ships by the hand of his servants, and servants
        who knew the sea. They went with the servants of Solomon to Ophir, and acquired
        four hundred and fifty talents of gold from there, and brought it to King
        Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Queen of Sheba\u2019s Praise of Solomon"
      title: "The Queen of Sheba\u2019s Praise of Solomon"
      number: 1
      content: 'Now when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came
        to Jerusalem to test Solomon with hard questions, having a very great retinue,
        camels that bore spices, gold in abundance, and precious stones; and when
        she came to Solomon, she spoke with him about all that was in her heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Solomon answered all her questions; there was nothing so difficult
        for Solomon that he could not explain it to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Solomon, the house
        that he had built, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: the food on his table, the seating of his servants, the service of
        his waiters and their apparel, his cupbearers and their apparel, and his
        entryway by which he went up to the house of the Lord, there was no more
        spirit in her.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then she said to the king: \u201CIt  was a true report which I heard
        in my own land about your words and your wisdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'However I did not believe their words until I came and saw with my
        own eyes; and indeed the half of the greatness of your wisdom was not told
        me. You exceed the fame of which I heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Happy are your men and happy are these your servants, who stand continually
        before you and hear your wisdom! '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Blessed be the Lord your God, who delighted in you, setting you on
        His throne to  be king for the Lord your God! Because your God has loved
        Israel, to establish them forever, therefore He made you king over them,
        to do justice and righteousness.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: And she gave the king one hundred and twenty talents of gold, spices
        in great abundance, and precious stones; there never were any spices such
        as those the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Also, the servants of Hiram and the servants of Solomon, who brought
        gold from Ophir, brought algum wood and precious stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the king made walkways of the algum wood for the house of the
        Lord and for the king\u2019s house, also harps and stringed instruments for
        singers; and there were none such as  these seen before in the land of Judah."
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Solomon\u2019s Great Wealth"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Great Wealth"
      number: 12
      content: Now King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all she desired, whatever
        she asked, much  more than she had brought to the king. So she turned and
        went to her own country, she and her servants.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The weight of gold that came to Solomon yearly was six hundred and
        sixty-six talents of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'besides what the traveling merchants and traders brought. And all
        the kings of Arabia and governors of the country brought gold and silver
        to Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And King Solomon made two hundred large shields of hammered gold;
        six hundred shekels of hammered gold went into each shield. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: He also made three hundred shields of hammered gold; three hundred
        shekels of gold went into each shield. The king put them in the House of
        the Forest of Lebanon.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with
        pure gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The throne had six steps, with a footstool of gold, which  were fastened
        to the throne; there were armrests on either side of the place of the seat,
        and two lions stood beside the armrests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Twelve lions stood there, one on each side of the six steps; nothing
        like this had been made for any other kingdom.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "All King Solomon\u2019s drinking vessels were gold, and all the vessels
        of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were pure gold. Not one  was silver,
        for this was accounted as nothing in the days of Solomon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "For the king\u2019s ships went to Tarshish with the servants of Hiram.
        Once every three years the merchant ships came, bringing gold, silver, ivory,
        apes, and monkeys."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So King Solomon surpassed all the kings of the earth in riches and
        wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And all the kings of the earth sought the presence of Solomon to
        hear his wisdom, which God had put in his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Each man brought his present: articles of silver and gold, garments,
        armor, spices, horses, and mules, at a set rate year by year.'
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Solomon had four thousand stalls for horses and chariots, and twelve
        thousand horsemen whom he stationed in the chariot cities and with the king
        at Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So he reigned over all the kings from the River to the land of the
        Philistines, as far as the border of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'The king made silver as  common in Jerusalem as stones, and he made
        cedar trees as abundant as the sycamores which are in the lowland. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Death of Solomon'
      title: Death of Solomon
      number: 28
      content: And they brought horses to Solomon from Egypt and from all lands.
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, first and last, are they not
        written in the book of Nathan the prophet, in the prophecy of Ahijah the
        Shilonite, and in the visions of Iddo the seer concerning Jeroboam the son
        of Nebat? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: Then Solomon rested with his fathers, and was buried in the City of
        David his father. And Rehoboam his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Revolt Against Rehoboam'
      title: The Revolt Against Rehoboam
      number: 1
      content: 'And Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had gone to Shechem
        to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So it happened, when Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard it (he was in
        Egypt, where he had fled from the presence of King Solomon), that Jeroboam
        returned from Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then they sent for him and called him. And Jeroboam and all Israel
        came and spoke to Rehoboam, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYour father made our yoke heavy; now therefore, lighten the
        burdensome service of your father and his heavy yoke which he put on us,
        and we will serve you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "So he said to them, \u201CCome back to me after three days.\u201D
        And the people departed."
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then King Rehoboam consulted the elders who stood before his father
        Solomon while he still lived, saying, \u201CHow do you advise me to answer
        these people?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they spoke to him, saying, \u201CIf you are kind to these people,
        and please them, and speak good words to them, they will be your servants
        forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But he rejected the advice which the elders had given him, and consulted
        the young men who had grown up with him, who stood before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CWhat advice do you give? How should we
        answer this people who have spoken to me, saying, \u2018Lighten the yoke
        which your father put on us\u2019?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then the young men who had grown up with him spoke to him, saying,
        \u201CThus you should speak to the people who have spoken to you, saying,
        \u2018Your father made our yoke heavy, but you make it lighter on us\u2019\u2014thus
        you shall say to them: \u2018My little finger shall be thicker than my father\u2019s
        waist! "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now, whereas my father put a heavy yoke on you, I will add to
        your yoke; my father chastised you with whips, but I will  chastise  you
        with scourges!\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam on the third day,
        as the king had directed, saying, \u201CCome back to me the third day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the king answered them roughly. King Rehoboam rejected the advice
        of the elders, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and he spoke to them according to the advice of the young men, saying,
        \u201CMy father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to it; my father chastised
        you with whips, but I will  chastise  you with scourges!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So the king did not listen to the people; for the turn of  events
        was from God, that the Lord might fulfill His word, which He had spoken by
        the hand of Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Now when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, the
        people answered the king, saying:\u201CWhat share have we in David?We  have
        no inheritance in the son of Jesse.Every man to your tents, O Israel!Now
        see to your own house, O David!\u201DSo all Israel departed to their tents. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But Rehoboam reigned over the children of Israel who dwelt in the
        cities of Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then King Rehoboam sent Hadoram, who was in charge of revenue; but
        the children of Israel stoned him with stones, and he died. Therefore King
        Rehoboam mounted his chariot in haste to flee to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this
        day.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: Now when Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled from the house of
        Judah and Benjamin one hundred and eighty thousand chosen men who were warriors,
        to fight against Israel, that he might restore the kingdom to Rehoboam.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But the word of the Lord came to Shemaiah the man of God, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CSpeak to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to
        all Israel in Judah and Benjamin, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Rehoboam Fortifies the Cities'
      title: Rehoboam Fortifies the Cities
      number: 4
      content: "\u2018Thus says the Lord: \u201CYou shall not go up or fight against
        your brethren! Let every man return to his house, for this thing is from
        Me.\u201D \u2019 \u201D Therefore they obeyed the words of the Lord, and
        turned back from attacking Jeroboam."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So Rehoboam dwelt in Jerusalem, and built cities for defense in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he built Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Beth Zur, Sochoh, Adullam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Gath, Mareshah, Ziph, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Zorah, Aijalon, and Hebron, which are in Judah and Benjamin, fortified
        cities. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And he fortified the strongholds, and put captains in them, and stores
        of food, oil, and wine. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Priests and Levites Move to Judah'
      title: Priests and Levites Move to Judah
      number: 12
      content: Also in every city he  put shields and spears, and made them very
        strong, having Judah and Benjamin on his side.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And from all their territories the priests and the Levites who were
        in all Israel took their stand with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the Levites left their common-lands and their possessions and
        came to Judah and Jerusalem, for Jeroboam and his sons had rejected them
        from serving as priests to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then he appointed for himself priests for the high places, for the
        demons, and the calf idols which he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And after the Levites left, those from all the tribes of Israel,
        such as set their heart to seek the Lord God of Israel, came to Jerusalem
        to sacrifice to the Lord God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: The Family of Rehoboam'
      title: The Family of Rehoboam
      number: 17
      content: So they strengthened the kingdom of Judah, and made Rehoboam the son
        of Solomon strong for three years, because they walked in the way of David
        and Solomon for three years.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then Rehoboam took for himself as wife Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth
        the son of David, and  of Abihail the daughter of Eliah the son of Jesse. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And she bore him children: Jeush, Shamariah, and Zaham. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After her he took Maachah the granddaughter of Absalom; and she bore
        him Abijah, Attai, Ziza, and Shelomith. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now Rehoboam loved Maachah the granddaughter of Absalom more than
        all his wives and his concubines; for he took eighteen wives and sixty concubines,
        and begot twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Rehoboam appointed Abijah the son of Maachah as chief, to  be
        leader among his brothers; for he intended to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: He dealt wisely, and dispersed some of his sons throughout all the
        territories of Judah and Benjamin, to every fortified city; and he gave them
        provisions in abundance. He also sought many wives for  them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Egypt Attacks Judah'
      title: Egypt Attacks Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now it came to pass, when Rehoboam had established the kingdom and
        had strengthened himself, that he forsook the law of the Lord, and all Israel
        along with him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And it happened in the fifth year of King Rehoboam that Shishak king
        of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, because they had transgressed against
        the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "with twelve hundred chariots, sixty thousand horsemen, and people
        without number who came with him out of Egypt\u2014the Lubim and the Sukkiim
        and the Ethiopians. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: And he took the fortified cities of Judah and came to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Shemaiah the prophet came to Rehoboam and the leaders of Judah,
        who were gathered together in Jerusalem because of Shishak, and said to them,
        \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018You have forsaken Me, and therefore I also
        have left you in the hand of Shishak.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the leaders of Israel and the king humbled themselves; and they
        said, \u201CThe Lord  is righteous.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now when the Lord saw that they humbled themselves, the word of the
        Lord came to Shemaiah, saying, \u201CThey have humbled themselves; therefore
        I will not destroy them, but I will grant them some deliverance. My wrath
        shall not be poured out on Jerusalem by the hand of Shishak. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Nevertheless they will be his servants, that they may distinguish
        My service from the service of the kingdoms of the nations.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, and took away
        the treasures of the house of the Lord and the treasures of the king\u2019s
        house; he took everything. He also carried away the gold shields which Solomon
        had made. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Then King Rehoboam made bronze shields in their place, and committed
        them  to the hands of the captains of the guard, who guarded the doorway
        of the king\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And whenever the king entered the house of the Lord, the guard would
        go and bring them out; then they would take them back into the guardroom. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: The End of Rehoboam\u2019s Reign"
      title: "The End of Rehoboam\u2019s Reign"
      number: 12
      content: When he humbled himself, the wrath of the Lord turned from him, so
        as not to destroy him completely; and things also went well in Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Thus King Rehoboam strengthened himself in Jerusalem and reigned.
        Now Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he became king; and he reigned
        seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city which the Lord had chosen out of all
        the tribes of Israel, to put His name there. His mother\u2019s name was Naamah,
        an Ammonitess. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: And he did evil, because he did not prepare his heart to seek the
        Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The acts of Rehoboam, first and last, are they not written in the
        book of Shemaiah the prophet, and of Iddo the seer concerning genealogies?
        And there  were wars between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all their days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: So Rehoboam rested with his fathers, and was buried in the City of
        David. Then Abijah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abijah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Abijah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam, Abijah became king over
        Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Michaiah
        the daughter of Uriel of Gibeah.And there was war between Abijah and Jeroboam. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Abijah set the battle in order with an army of valiant warriors, four
        hundred thousand choice men. Jeroboam also drew up in battle formation against
        him with eight hundred thousand choice men, mighty men of valor.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Abijah stood on Mount Zemaraim, which is in the mountains of
        Ephraim, and said, \u201CHear me, Jeroboam and all Israel: "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Should you not know that the Lord God of Israel gave the dominion
        over Israel to David forever, to him and his sons, by a covenant of salt? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Yet Jeroboam the son of Nebat, the servant of Solomon the son of
        David, rose up and rebelled against his lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then worthless rogues gathered to him, and strengthened themselves
        against Rehoboam the son of Solomon, when Rehoboam was young and inexperienced
        and could not withstand them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And now you think to withstand the kingdom of the Lord, which is
        in the hand of the sons of David; and you are a great multitude, and with
        you are the gold calves which Jeroboam made for you as gods. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Have you not cast out the priests of the Lord, the sons of Aaron,
        and the Levites, and made for yourselves priests, like the peoples of other
        lands, so that whoever comes to consecrate himself with a young bull and
        seven rams may be a priest of things  that  are not gods? '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But as for us, the Lord  is our God, and we have not forsaken Him;
        and the priests who minister to the Lord  are the sons of Aaron, and the
        Levites attend to their duties. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they burn to the Lord every morning and every evening burnt sacrifices
        and sweet incense; they also set the showbread in  order  on the pure gold
        table, and the lampstand of gold with its lamps to burn every evening; for
        we keep the command of the Lord our God, but you have forsaken Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Now look, God Himself is with us as our  head, and His priests with
        sounding trumpets to sound the alarm against you. O children of Israel, do
        not fight against the Lord God of your fathers, for you shall not prosper!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'But Jeroboam caused an ambush to go around behind them; so they were
        in front of Judah, and the ambush was behind them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And when Judah looked around, to their surprise the battle line was
        at both front and rear; and they cried out to the Lord, and the priests sounded
        the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then the men of Judah gave a shout; and as the men of Judah shouted,
        it happened that God struck Jeroboam and all Israel before Abijah and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And the children of Israel fled before Judah, and God delivered them
        into their hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then Abijah and his people struck them with a great slaughter; so
        five hundred thousand choice men of Israel fell slain. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Thus the children of Israel were subdued at that time; and the children
        of Judah prevailed, because they relied on the Lord God of their fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Abijah pursued Jeroboam and took cities from him: Bethel with
        its villages, Jeshanah with its villages, and Ephrain with its villages. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: So Jeroboam did not recover strength again in the days of Abijah;
        and the Lord  struck him, and he died.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But Abijah grew mighty, married fourteen wives, and begot twenty-two
        sons and sixteen daughters. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Abijah, his ways, and his sayings are
        written in the annals of the prophet Iddo.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Asa Reigns in Judah'
      title: Asa Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: So Abijah rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the City
        of David. Then Asa his son reigned in his place. In his days the land was
        quiet for ten years.
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Asa did what  was good and right in the eyes of the Lord his God, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'for he removed the altars of the foreign gods and the high places,
        and broke down the sacred pillars and cut down the wooden images. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He commanded Judah to seek the Lord God of their fathers, and to
        observe the law and the commandment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also removed the high places and the incense altars from all the
        cities of Judah, and the kingdom was quiet under him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he built fortified cities in Judah, for the land had rest; he
        had no war in those years, because the Lord had given him rest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore he said to Judah, \u201CLet us build these cities and make
        walls around them, and towers, gates, and bars, while the land is yet before
        us, because we have sought the Lord our God; we have sought Him, and He has
        given us rest on every side.\u201D So they built and prospered. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: And Asa had an army of three hundred thousand from Judah who carried
        shields and spears, and from Benjamin two hundred and eighty thousand men
        who carried shields and drew bows; all these were mighty men of valor.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Zerah the Ethiopian came out against them with an army of a
        million men and three hundred chariots, and he came to Mareshah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Asa went out against him, and they set the troops in battle array
        in the Valley of Zephathah at Mareshah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Asa cried out to the Lord his God, and said, \u201CLord, it 
        is  nothing for You to help, whether with many or with those who have no
        power; help us, O Lord our God, for we rest on You, and in Your name we go
        against this multitude. O Lord, You are our God; do not let man prevail against
        You!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So the Lord  struck the Ethiopians before Asa and Judah, and the
        Ethiopians fled. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And Asa and the people who were with him pursued them to Gerar. So
        the Ethiopians were overthrown, and they could not recover, for they were
        broken before the Lord and His army. And they carried away very much spoil. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then they defeated all the cities around Gerar, for the fear of the
        Lord came upon them; and they plundered all the cities, for there was exceedingly
        much spoil in them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: They also attacked the livestock enclosures, and carried off sheep
        and camels in abundance, and returned to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Reforms of Asa'
      title: The Reforms of Asa
      number: 1
      content: 'Now the Spirit of God came upon Azariah the son of Oded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he went out to meet Asa, and said to him: \u201CHear me, Asa,
        and all Judah and Benjamin. The Lord  is with you while you are with Him.
        If you seek Him, He will be found by you; but if you forsake Him, He will
        forsake you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For a long time Israel has  been without the true God, without a
        teaching priest, and without law; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but when in their trouble they turned to the Lord God of Israel,
        and sought Him, He was found by them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And in those times there  was no peace to the one who went out, nor
        to the one who came in, but great turmoil was on all the inhabitants of the
        lands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So nation was destroyed by nation, and city by city, for God troubled
        them with every adversity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But you, be strong and do not let your hands be weak, for your work
        shall be rewarded!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when Asa heard these words and the prophecy of Oded the prophet,
        he took courage, and removed the abominable idols from all the land of Judah
        and Benjamin and from the cities which he had taken in the mountains of Ephraim;
        and he restored the altar of the Lord that was before the vestibule of the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Then he gathered all Judah and Benjamin, and those who dwelt with
        them from Ephraim, Manasseh, and Simeon, for they came over to him in great
        numbers from Israel when they saw that the Lord his God was with him.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So they gathered together at Jerusalem in the third month, in the
        fifteenth year of the reign of Asa. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they offered to the Lord at that time seven hundred bulls and
        seven thousand sheep from the spoil they had brought. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then they entered into a covenant to seek the Lord God of their fathers
        with all their heart and with all their soul; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and whoever would not seek the Lord God of Israel was to be put to
        death, whether small or great, whether man or woman. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then they took an oath before the Lord with a loud voice, with shouting
        and trumpets and rams\u2019 horns. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And all Judah rejoiced at the oath, for they had sworn with all their
        heart and sought Him with all their soul; and He was found by them, and the
        Lord gave them rest all around.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Also he removed Maachah, the mother of Asa the king, from being queen
        mother, because she had made an obscene image of Asherah; and Asa cut down
        her obscene image, then crushed and burned it by the Brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: But the high places were not removed from Israel. Nevertheless the
        heart of Asa was loyal all his days.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'He also brought into the house of God the things that his father
        had dedicated and that he himself had dedicated: silver and gold and utensils. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And there was no war until the thirty-fifth year of the reign of Asa.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Asa\u2019s Treaty with Syria"
      title: "Asa\u2019s Treaty with Syria"
      number: 1
      content: 'In the thirty-sixth year of the reign of Asa, Baasha king of Israel
        came up against Judah and built Ramah, that he might let none go out or come
        in to Asa king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Asa brought silver and gold from the treasuries of the house
        of the Lord and of the king\u2019s house, and sent to Ben-Hadad king of Syria,
        who dwelt in Damascus, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CLet  there  be a treaty between you and me, as there was between
        my father and your father. See, I have sent you silver and gold; come, break
        your treaty with Baasha king of Israel, so that he will withdraw from me.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Ben-Hadad heeded King Asa, and sent the captains of his armies
        against the cities of Israel. They attacked Ijon, Dan, Abel Maim, and all
        the storage cities of Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now it happened, when Baasha heard it, that he stopped building Ramah
        and ceased his work. '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: Hanani\u2019s Message to Asa"
      title: "Hanani\u2019s Message to Asa"
      number: 6
      content: Then King Asa took all Judah, and they carried away the stones and
        timber of Ramah, which Baasha had used for building; and with them he built
        Geba and Mizpah.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And at that time Hanani the seer came to Asa king of Judah, and said
        to him: \u201CBecause you have relied on the king of Syria, and have not
        relied on the Lord your God, therefore the army of the king of Syria has
        escaped from your hand. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Were the Ethiopians and the Lubim not a huge army with very many
        chariots and horsemen? Yet, because you relied on the Lord, He delivered
        them into your hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For the eyes of the Lord run to and fro throughout the whole earth,
        to show Himself strong on behalf of those whose heart is loyal to Him. In
        this you have done foolishly; therefore from now on you shall have wars.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Illness and Death of Asa'
      title: Illness and Death of Asa
      number: 10
      content: Then Asa was angry with the seer, and put him in prison, for he  was
        enraged at him because of this. And Asa oppressed some of the people at that
        time.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Note that the acts of Asa, first and last, are indeed written in
        the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And in the thirty-ninth year of his reign, Asa became diseased in
        his feet, and his malady was severe; yet in his disease he did not seek the
        Lord, but the physicians.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So Asa rested with his fathers; he died in the forty-first year of
        his reign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: They buried him in his own tomb, which he had made for himself in
        the City of David; and they laid him in the bed which was filled with spices
        and various ingredients prepared in a mixture of ointments. They made a very
        great burning for him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoshaphat Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoshaphat Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place, and strengthened himself
        against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he placed troops in all the fortified cities of Judah, and set
        garrisons in the land of Judah and in the cities of Ephraim which Asa his
        father had taken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the Lord was with Jehoshaphat, because he walked in the former
        ways of his father David; he did not seek the Baals, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but sought the God of his father, and walked in His commandments
        and not according to the acts of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore the Lord established the kingdom in his hand; and all Judah
        gave presents to Jehoshaphat, and he had riches and honor in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And his heart took delight in the ways of the Lord; moreover he removed
        the high places and wooden images from Judah.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Also in the third year of his reign he sent his leaders, Ben-Hail,
        Obadiah, Zechariah, Nethanel, and Michaiah, to teach in the cities of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And with them he  sent Levites: Shemaiah, Nethaniah, Zebadiah, Asahel,
        Shemiramoth, Jehonathan, Adonijah, Tobijah, and Tobadonijah\u2014the Levites;
        and with them Elishama and Jehoram, the priests. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So they taught in Judah, and had the Book of the Law of the Lord with
        them; they went throughout all the cities of Judah and taught the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the fear of the Lord fell on all the kingdoms of the lands that
        were around Judah, so that they did not make war against Jehoshaphat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Also some of the Philistines brought Jehoshaphat presents and silver
        as tribute; and the Arabians brought him flocks, seven thousand seven hundred
        rams and seven thousand seven hundred male goats.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So Jehoshaphat became increasingly powerful, and he built fortresses
        and storage cities in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: He had much property in the cities of Judah; and the men of war, mighty
        men of valor, were in Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "These are their numbers, according to their fathers\u2019 houses.
        Of Judah, the captains of thousands: Adnah the captain, and with him three
        hundred thousand mighty men of valor; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and next to him was Jehohanan the captain, and with him two hundred
        and eighty thousand; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'and next to him was Amasiah the son of Zichri, who willingly offered
        himself to the Lord, and with him two hundred thousand mighty men of valor. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Of Benjamin: Eliada a mighty man of valor, and with him two hundred
        thousand men armed with bow and shield; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and next to him was Jehozabad, and with him one hundred and eighty
        thousand prepared for war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: These served the king, besides those the king put in the fortified
        cities throughout all Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Micaiah Warns Ahab'
      title: Micaiah Warns Ahab
      number: 1
      content: 'Jehoshaphat had riches and honor in abundance; and by marriage he
        allied himself with Ahab. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'After some years he went down to visit Ahab in Samaria; and Ahab
        killed sheep and oxen in abundance for him and the people who were with him,
        and persuaded him to go up with  him to Ramoth Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So Ahab king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, \u201CWill
        you go with me against Ramoth Gilead?\u201DAnd he answered him, \u201CI am
        as you are, and my people as your people; we  will  be with you in the war.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Also Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, \u201CPlease inquire
        for the word of the Lord today.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, four hundred
        men, and said to them, \u201CShall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or
        shall I refrain?\u201DSo they said, \u201CGo up, for God will deliver it
        into the king\u2019s hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But Jehoshaphat said, \u201CIs  there not still a prophet of the
        Lord here, that we may inquire of Him?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CThere  is still
        one man by whom we may inquire of the Lord; but I hate him, because he never
        prophesies good concerning me, but always evil. He is Micaiah the son of
        Imla.\u201DAnd Jehoshaphat said, \u201CLet not the king say such things!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then the king of Israel called one of  his officers and said, \u201CBring
        Micaiah the son of Imla quickly!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah, clothed in their
        robes, sat each on his throne; and they sat at a threshing floor at the entrance
        of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets prophesied before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Now Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah had made horns of iron for himself;
        and he said, \u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018With these you shall gore the
        Syrians until they are destroyed.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And all the prophets prophesied so, saying, \u201CGo up to Ramoth
        Gilead and prosper, for the Lord will deliver it into the king\u2019s hand.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the messenger who had gone to call Micaiah spoke to him, saying,
        \u201CNow listen, the words of the prophets with one accord encourage the
        king. Therefore please let your word be like the  word  of one of them, and
        speak encouragement.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Micaiah said, \u201CAs the Lord lives, whatever my God says,
        that I will speak.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he came to the king; and the king said to him, \u201CMicaiah,
        shall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or shall I refrain?\u201DAnd he
        said, \u201CGo and prosper, and they shall be delivered into your hand!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So the king said to him, \u201CHow many times shall I make you swear
        that you tell me nothing but the truth in the name of the Lord?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI saw all Israel scattered on the mountains,
        as sheep that have no shepherd. And the Lord said, \u2018These have no master.
        Let each return to his house in peace.\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CDid I not tell
        you he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Micaiah said, \u201CTherefore hear the word of the Lord: I saw
        the Lord sitting on His throne, and all the host of heaven standing on His
        right hand and His left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And the Lord said, \u2018Who will persuade Ahab king of Israel to
        go up, that he may fall at Ramoth Gilead?\u2019 So one spoke in this manner,
        and another spoke in that manner. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then a spirit came forward and stood before the Lord, and said, \u2018I
        will persuade him.\u2019 The Lord said to him, \u2018In what way?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "So he said, \u2018I will go out and be a lying spirit in the mouth
        of all his prophets.\u2019 And the  Lord said, \u2018You shall persuade him
        and also prevail; go out and do so.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore look! The Lord has put a lying spirit in the mouth of these
        prophets of yours, and the Lord has declared disaster against you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah went near and struck Micaiah on
        the cheek, and said, \u201CWhich way did the spirit from the Lord go from
        me to speak to you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Micaiah said, \u201CIndeed you shall see on that day when you
        go into an inner chamber to hide!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then the king of Israel said, \u201CTake Micaiah, and return him
        to Amon the governor of the city and to Joash the king\u2019s son; "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the king: \u201CPut this fellow in prison,
        and feed him with bread of affliction and water of affliction, until I return
        in peace.\u201D \u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Ahab Dies in Battle'
      title: Ahab Dies in Battle
      number: 27
      content: "But Micaiah said, \u201CIf you ever return in peace, the Lord has
        not spoken by me.\u201D And he said, \u201CTake heed, all you people!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to
        Ramoth Gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CI will disguise
        myself and go into battle; but you put on your robes.\u201D So the king of
        Israel disguised himself, and they went into battle."
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Now the king of Syria had commanded the captains of the chariots
        who were with him, saying, \u201CFight with no one small or great, but only
        with the king of Israel.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So it was, when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, that
        they said, \u201CIt is the king of Israel!\u201D Therefore they surrounded
        him to attack; but Jehoshaphat cried out, and the Lord helped him, and God
        diverted them from him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'For so it was, when the captains of the chariots saw that it was
        not the king of Israel, that they turned back from pursuing him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Now a certain man drew a bow at random, and struck the king of Israel
        between the joints of his armor. So he said to the driver of his chariot,
        \u201CTurn around and take me out of the battle, for I am wounded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: The battle increased that day, and the king of Israel propped himself
        up in his chariot facing the Syrians until evening; and about the time of
        sunset he died.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: 'Then Jehoshaphat the king of Judah returned safely to his house in
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jehu the son of Hanani the seer went out to meet him, and said
        to King Jehoshaphat, \u201CShould you help the wicked and love those who
        hate the Lord? Therefore the wrath of the Lord  is upon you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Reforms of Jehoshaphat'
      title: The Reforms of Jehoshaphat
      number: 3
      content: "Nevertheless good things are found in you, in that you have removed
        the wooden images from the land, and have prepared your heart to seek God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'So Jehoshaphat dwelt at Jerusalem; and he went out again among the
        people from Beersheba to the mountains of Ephraim, and brought them back
        to the Lord God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then he set judges in the land throughout all the fortified cities
        of Judah, city by city, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and said to the judges, \u201CTake heed to what you are doing, for
        you do not judge for man but for the Lord, who is with you in the judgment. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore, let the fear of the Lord be upon you; take care and
        do it, for there  is no iniquity with the Lord our God, no partiality, nor
        taking of bribes.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Moreover in Jerusalem, for the judgment of the Lord and for controversies,
        Jehoshaphat appointed some of the Levites and priests, and some of the chief
        fathers of Israel, when they returned to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he commanded them, saying, \u201CThus you shall act in the fear
        of the Lord, faithfully and with a loyal heart: "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Whatever case comes to you from your brethren who dwell in their
        cities, whether of bloodshed or offenses against law or commandment, against
        statutes or ordinances, you shall warn them, lest they trespass against the
        Lord and wrath come upon you and your brethren. Do this, and you will not
        be guilty. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And take notice: Amariah the chief priest is over you in all matters
        of the Lord; and Zebadiah the son of Ishmael, the ruler of the house of Judah,
        for all the king\u2019s matters; also the Levites will  be officials before
        you. Behave courageously, and the Lord will be with the good.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir Defeated'
      title: Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir Defeated
      number: 1
      content: 'It happened after this that the people of Moab with the people of
        Ammon, and others with them besides the Ammonites, came to battle against
        Jehoshaphat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then some came and told Jehoshaphat, saying, \u201CA great multitude
        is coming against you from beyond the sea, from Syria; and they are in Hazazon
        Tamar\u201D (which is  En Gedi). "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat feared, and set himself to seek the Lord, and proclaimed
        a fast throughout all Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: So Judah gathered together to ask help from the Lord; and from all
        the cities of Judah they came to seek the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then Jehoshaphat stood in the assembly of Judah and Jerusalem, in
        the house of the Lord, before the new court, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "and said: \u201CO Lord God of our fathers, are You not God in heaven,
        and do You not rule over all the kingdoms of the nations, and in Your hand
        is  there  not power and might, so that no one is able to withstand You? "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Are You not our God, who  drove out the inhabitants of this land
        before Your people Israel, and gave it to the descendants of Abraham Your
        friend forever? '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And they dwell in it, and have built You a sanctuary in it for Your
        name, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u2018If disaster comes upon us\u2014sword, judgment, pestilence,
        or famine\u2014we will stand before this temple and in Your presence (for
        Your name is in this temple), and cry out to You in our affliction, and You
        will hear and save.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And now, here are the people of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir\u2014whom
        You would not let Israel invade when they came out of the land of Egypt,
        but they turned from them and did not destroy them\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'here they are, rewarding us by coming to throw us out of Your possession
        which You have given us to inherit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "O our God, will You not judge them? For we have no power against
        this great multitude that is coming against us; nor do we know what to do,
        but our eyes are upon You.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: Now all Judah, with their little ones, their wives, and their children,
        stood before the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon Jahaziel the son of Zechariah,
        the son of Benaiah, the son of Jeiel, the son of Mattaniah, a Levite of the
        sons of Asaph, in the midst of the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said, \u201CListen, all you of Judah and you inhabitants of
        Jerusalem, and you, King Jehoshaphat! Thus says the Lord to you: \u2018Do
        not be afraid nor dismayed because of this great multitude, for the battle
        is not yours, but God\u2019s. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Tomorrow go down against them. They will surely come up by the Ascent
        of Ziz, and you will find them at the end of the brook before the Wilderness
        of Jeruel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "You will not need to fight in this battle. Position yourselves, stand
        still and see the salvation of the Lord, who is with you, O Judah and Jerusalem!\u2019
        Do not fear or be dismayed; tomorrow go out against them, for the Lord  is
        with you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat bowed his head with his face to the ground, and all
        Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem bowed before the Lord, worshiping
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then the Levites of the children of the Kohathites and of the children
        of the Korahites stood up to praise the Lord God of Israel with voices loud
        and high.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So they rose early in the morning and went out into the Wilderness
        of Tekoa; and as they went out, Jehoshaphat stood and said, \u201CHear me,
        O Judah and you inhabitants of Jerusalem: Believe in the Lord your God, and
        you shall be established; believe His prophets, and you shall prosper.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And when he had consulted with the people, he appointed those who
        should sing to the Lord, and who should praise the beauty of holiness, as
        they went out before the army and were saying:\u201CPraise the Lord,For His
        mercy endures forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now when they began to sing and to praise, the Lord set ambushes
        against the people of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir, who had come against Judah;
        and they were defeated. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: For the people of Ammon and Moab stood up against the inhabitants
        of Mount Seir to utterly kill and destroy them. And when they had made an
        end of the inhabitants of Seir, they helped to destroy one another.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: So when Judah came to a place overlooking the wilderness, they looked
        toward the multitude; and there were their dead bodies, fallen on the earth.
        No one had escaped.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When Jehoshaphat and his people came to take away their spoil, they
        found among them an abundance of valuables on the dead bodies, and precious
        jewelry, which they stripped off for themselves, more than they could carry
        away; and they were three days gathering the spoil because there was so much. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'And on the fourth day they assembled in the Valley of Berachah, for
        there they blessed the Lord; therefore the name of that place was called
        The Valley of Berachah until this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then they returned, every man of Judah and Jerusalem, with Jehoshaphat
        in front of them, to go back to Jerusalem with joy, for the Lord had made
        them rejoice over their enemies. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So they came to Jerusalem, with stringed instruments and harps and
        trumpets, to the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the fear of God was on all the kingdoms of those countries when
        they heard that the Lord had fought against the enemies of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "30: The End of Jehoshaphat\u2019s Reign"
      title: "The End of Jehoshaphat\u2019s Reign"
      number: 30
      content: Then the realm of Jehoshaphat was quiet, for his God gave him rest
        all around.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "So Jehoshaphat was king over Judah. He  was thirty-five years old
        when he became king, and he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s
        name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he walked in the way of his father Asa, and did not turn aside
        from it, doing what  was right in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Nevertheless the high places were not taken away, for as yet the people
        had not directed their hearts to the God of their fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, first and last, indeed they
        are written in the book of Jehu the son of Hanani, which is mentioned in
        the book of the kings of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'After this Jehoshaphat king of Judah allied himself with Ahaziah
        king of Israel, who acted very wickedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And he allied himself with him to make ships to go to Tarshish, and
        they made the ships in Ezion Geber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "But Eliezer the son of Dodavah of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat,
        saying, \u201CBecause you have allied yourself with Ahaziah, the Lord has
        destroyed your works.\u201D Then the ships were wrecked, so that they were
        not able to go to Tarshish."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jehoram Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoram Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat rested with his fathers, and was buried with his
        fathers in the City of David. Then Jehoram his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He had brothers, the sons of Jehoshaphat: Azariah, Jehiel, Zechariah,
        Azaryahu, Michael, and Shephatiah; all these were the sons of Jehoshaphat
        king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: Their father gave them great gifts of silver and gold and precious
        things, with fortified cities in Judah; but he gave the kingdom to Jehoram,
        because he was the firstborn.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Now when Jehoram was established over the kingdom of his father, he
        strengthened himself and killed all his brothers with the sword, and also
        others of the princes of Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Jehoram was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eight years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, just as the house
        of Ahab had done, for he had the daughter of Ahab as a wife; and he did evil
        in the sight of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: Yet the Lord would not destroy the house of David, because of the
        covenant that He had made with David, and since He had promised to give a
        lamp to him and to his sons forever.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "In his days Edom revolted against Judah\u2019s authority, and made
        a king over themselves. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So Jehoram went out with his officers, and all his chariots with
        him. And he rose by night and attacked the Edomites who had surrounded him
        and the captains of the chariots. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Thus Edom has been in revolt against Judah\u2019s authority to this
        day. At that time Libnah revolted against his rule, because he had forsaken
        the Lord God of his fathers. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Moreover he made high places in the mountains of Judah, and caused
        the inhabitants of Jerusalem to commit harlotry, and led Judah astray.
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And a letter came to him from Elijah the prophet, saying,Thus says
        the Lord God of your father David:Because you have not walked in the ways
        of Jehoshaphat your father, or in the ways of Asa king of Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "but have walked in the way of the kings of Israel, and have made
        Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to play the harlot like the harlotry
        of the house of Ahab, and also have killed your brothers, those of your father\u2019s
        household, who  were better than yourself, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "behold, the Lord will strike your people with a serious affliction\u2014your
        children, your wives, and all your possessions; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: and you will  become very sick with a disease of your intestines,
        until your intestines come out by reason of the sickness, day by day.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Moreover the Lord  stirred up against Jehoram the spirit of the Philistines
        and the Arabians who were near the Ethiopians. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they came up into Judah and invaded it, and carried away all
        the possessions that were found in the king\u2019s house, and also his sons
        and his wives, so that there was not a son left to him except Jehoahaz, the
        youngest of his sons."
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'After all this the Lord struck him in his intestines with an incurable
        disease. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Then it happened in the course of time, after the end of two years,
        that his intestines came out because of his sickness; so he died in severe
        pain. And his people made no burning for him, like the burning for his fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "He was thirty-two years old when he became king. He reigned in Jerusalem
        eight years and, to no one\u2019s sorrow, departed. However they buried him
        in the City of David, but not in the tombs of the kings."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaziah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Ahaziah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Then the inhabitants of Jerusalem made Ahaziah his youngest son king
        in his place, for the raiders who came with the Arabians into the camp had
        killed all the older sons. So Ahaziah the son of Jehoram, king of Judah,
        reigned. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Ahaziah was forty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        one year in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was  Athaliah the granddaughter
        of Omri. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He also walked in the ways of the house of Ahab, for his mother advised
        him to do wickedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Therefore he did evil in the sight of the Lord, like the house of
        Ahab; for they were his counselors after the death of his father, to his
        destruction. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also followed their advice, and went with Jehoram the son of Ahab
        king of Israel to war against Hazael king of Syria at Ramoth Gilead; and
        the Syrians wounded Joram. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Then he returned to Jezreel to recover from the wounds which he had
        received at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of Syria. And Azariah
        the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, went down to see Jehoram the son of Ahab
        in Jezreel, because he was sick.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "His going to Joram was God\u2019s occasion for Ahaziah\u2019s downfall;
        for when he arrived, he went out with Jehoram against Jehu the son of Nimshi,
        whom the Lord had anointed to cut off the house of Ahab. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And it happened, when Jehu was executing judgment on the house of
        Ahab, and found the princes of Judah and the sons of Ahaziah\u2019s brothers
        who served Ahaziah, that he killed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Athaliah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Athaliah Reigns in Judah
      number: 9
      content: "Then he searched for Ahaziah; and they caught him (he was hiding
        in Samaria), and brought him to Jehu. When they had killed him, they buried
        him, \u201Cbecause,\u201D they said, \u201Che is the son of Jehoshaphat,
        who sought the Lord with all his heart.\u201DSo the house of Ahaziah had
        no one to assume power over the kingdom."
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead,
        she arose and destroyed all the royal heirs of the house of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "But Jehoshabeath, the daughter of the king, took Joash the son of
        Ahaziah, and stole him away from among the king\u2019s sons who were being
        murdered, and put him and his nurse in a bedroom. So Jehoshabeath, the daughter
        of King Jehoram, the wife of Jehoiada the priest (for she was the sister
        of Ahaziah), hid him from Athaliah so that she did not kill him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: And he was hidden with them in the house of God for six years, while
        Athaliah reigned over the land.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joash Crowned King of Judah'
      title: Joash Crowned King of Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'In the seventh year Jehoiada strengthened himself, and  made  a covenant
        with the captains of hundreds: Azariah the son of Jeroham, Ishmael the son
        of Jehohanan, Azariah the son of Obed, Maaseiah the son of Adaiah, and Elishaphat
        the son of Zichri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And they went throughout Judah and gathered the Levites from all the
        cities of Judah, and the chief fathers of Israel, and they came to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then all the assembly made a covenant with the king in the house
        of God. And he said to them, \u201CBehold, the king\u2019s son shall reign,
        as the Lord has said of the sons of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'This is what you shall do: One-third of you entering on the Sabbath,
        of the priests and the Levites, shall  be keeping watch over the doors; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "one-third shall  be at the king\u2019s house; and one-third at the
        Gate of the Foundation. All the people shall  be in the courts of the house
        of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But let no one come into the house of the Lord except the priests
        and those of the Levites who serve. They may go in, for they are holy; but
        all the people shall keep the watch of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the Levites shall surround the king on all sides, every man with
        his weapons in his hand; and whoever comes into the house, let him be put
        to death. You are to be with the king when he comes in and when he goes out.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the Levites and all Judah did according to all that Jehoiada the
        priest commanded. And each man took his men who were to be on duty on the
        Sabbath, with those who were going off  duty on the Sabbath; for Jehoiada
        the priest had not dismissed the divisions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Jehoiada the priest gave to the captains of hundreds the spears
        and the large and small shields which had  belonged to King David, that were
        in the temple of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then he set all the people, every man with his weapon in his hand,
        from the right side of the temple to the left side of the temple, along by
        the altar and by the temple, all around the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Death of Athaliah'
      title: Death of Athaliah
      number: 11
      content: "And they brought out the king\u2019s son, put the crown on him, gave 
        him the Testimony, and made him king. Then Jehoiada and his sons anointed
        him, and said, \u201CLong live the king!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and praising
        the king, she came to the people in the temple of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When she looked, there was the king standing by his pillar at the
        entrance; and the leaders and the trumpeters were by the king. All the people
        of the land were rejoicing and blowing trumpets, also the singers with musical
        instruments, and those who led in praise. So Athaliah tore her clothes and
        said, \u201CTreason! Treason!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Jehoiada the priest brought out the captains of hundreds who
        were set over the army, and said to them, \u201CTake her outside under guard,
        and slay with the sword whoever follows her.\u201D For the priest had said,
        \u201CDo not kill her in the house of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "So they seized her; and she went by way of the entrance of the Horse
        Gate into the king\u2019s house, and they killed her there."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Then Jehoiada made a covenant between himself, the people, and the
        king, that they should be the Lord\u2019s people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And all the people went to the temple of Baal, and tore it down.
        They broke in pieces its altars and images, and killed Mattan the priest
        of Baal before the altars. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Also Jehoiada appointed the oversight of the house of the Lord to
        the hand of the priests, the Levites, whom David had assigned in the house
        of the Lord, to offer the burnt offerings of the Lord, as it  is written
        in the Law of Moses, with rejoicing and with singing, as  it  was  established
        by David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: And he set the gatekeepers at the gates of the house of the Lord,
        so that no one who  was in any way unclean should enter.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then he took the captains of hundreds, the nobles, the governors
        of the people, and all the people of the land, and brought the king down
        from the house of the Lord; and they went through the Upper Gate to the king\u2019s
        house, and set the king on the throne of the kingdom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: So all the people of the land rejoiced; and the city was quiet, for
        they had slain Athaliah with the sword.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Joash Repairs the Temple'
      title: Joash Repairs the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "Joash was seven years old when he became king, and he reigned forty
        years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Zibiah of Beersheba. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Joash did what  was right in the sight of the Lord all the days of
        Jehoiada the priest. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: And Jehoiada took two wives for him, and he had sons and daughters.
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Now it happened after this that Joash set his heart on repairing
        the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then he gathered the priests and the Levites, and said to them, \u201CGo
        out to the cities of Judah, and gather from all Israel money to repair the
        house of your God from year to year, and see that you do it quickly.\u201DHowever
        the Levites did not do it quickly. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the king called Jehoiada the chief priest, and said to him, \u201CWhy
        have you not required the Levites to bring in from Judah and from Jerusalem
        the collection, according  to  the  commandment of Moses the servant of the
        Lord and of the assembly of Israel, for the tabernacle of witness?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: For the sons of Athaliah, that wicked woman, had broken into the house
        of God, and had also presented all the dedicated things of the house of the
        Lord to the Baals.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then at the king\u2019s command they made a chest, and set it outside
        at the gate of the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And they made a proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem to bring
        to the Lord  the collection that Moses the servant of God had  imposed on
        Israel in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then all the leaders and all the people rejoiced, brought their contributions,
        and put them into the chest until all had given. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "So it was, at that time, when the chest was brought to the king\u2019s
        official by the hand of the Levites, and when they saw that there  was much
        money, that the king\u2019s scribe and the high priest\u2019s officer came
        and emptied the chest, and took it and returned it to its place. Thus they
        did day by day, and gathered money in abundance."
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The king and Jehoiada gave it to those who did the work of the service
        of the house of the Lord; and they hired masons and carpenters to repair
        the house of the Lord, and also those who worked in iron and bronze to restore
        the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'So the workmen labored, and the work was completed by them; they
        restored the house of God to its original condition and reinforced it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Apostasy of Joash'
      title: Apostasy of Joash
      number: 14
      content: When they had finished, they brought the rest of the money before
        the king and Jehoiada; they made from it articles for the house of the Lord,
        articles for serving and offering, spoons and vessels of gold and silver.
        And they offered burnt offerings in the house of the Lord continually all
        the days of Jehoiada.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But Jehoiada grew old and was full of days, and he died; he  was
        one hundred and thirty years old when he died. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And they buried him in the City of David among the kings, because
        he had done good in Israel, both toward God and His house.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now after the death of Jehoiada the leaders of Judah came and bowed
        down to the king. And the king listened to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore they left the house of the Lord God of their fathers, and
        served wooden images and idols; and wrath came upon Judah and Jerusalem because
        of their trespass. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Yet He sent prophets to them, to bring them back to the Lord; and
        they testified against them, but they would not listen.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then the Spirit of God came upon Zechariah the son of Jehoiada the
        priest, who stood above the people, and said to them, \u201CThus says God:
        \u2018Why do you transgress the commandments of the Lord, so that you cannot
        prosper? Because you have forsaken the Lord, He also has forsaken you.\u2019
        \u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So they conspired against him, and at the command of the king they
        stoned him with stones in the court of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: Death of Joash'
      title: Death of Joash
      number: 22
      content: "Thus Joash the king did not remember the kindness which Jehoiada
        his father had done to him, but killed his son; and as he died, he said,
        \u201CThe Lord look on it, and repay!\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'So it happened in the spring of the year that  the army of Syria
        came up against him; and they came to Judah and Jerusalem, and destroyed
        all the leaders of the people from among the people, and sent all their spoil
        to the king of Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For the army of the Syrians came with a small company of men; but
        the Lord  delivered a very great army into their hand, because they had forsaken
        the Lord God of their fathers. So they executed judgment against Joash. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And when they had withdrawn from him (for they left him severely wounded),
        his own servants conspired against him because of the blood of the sons of
        Jehoiada the priest, and killed him on his bed. So he died. And they buried
        him in the City of David, but they did not bury him in the tombs of the kings.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'These are the ones who conspired against him: Zabad the son of Shimeath
        the Ammonitess, and Jehozabad the son of Shimrith the Moabitess. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Now concerning his sons, and the many oracles about him, and the repairing
        of the house of God, indeed they are written in the annals of the book of
        the kings. Then Amaziah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Amaziah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Amaziah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "Amaziah was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, but not with
        a loyal heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now it happened, as soon as the kingdom was established for him,
        that he executed his servants who had murdered his father the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The War Against Edom'
      title: The War Against Edom
      number: 4
      content: "However he did not execute their children, but did as it  is written
        in the Law in the Book of Moses, where the Lord commanded, saying, \u201CThe
        fathers shall not be put to death for their children, nor shall the children
        be put to death for their fathers; but a person shall die for his own sin.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Moreover Amaziah gathered Judah together and set over them captains
        of thousands and captains of hundreds, according to their fathers\u2019 houses,
        throughout all Judah and Benjamin; and he numbered them from twenty years
        old and above, and found them to be three hundred thousand choice men, able
        to go to war, who could handle spear and shield. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He also hired one hundred thousand mighty men of valor from Israel
        for one hundred talents of silver. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But a man of God came to him, saying, \u201CO king, do not let the
        army of Israel go with you, for the Lord  is not with Israel\u2014not  with
        any of the children of Ephraim. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But if you go, be gone! Be strong in battle! Even  so, God shall
        make you fall before the enemy; for God has power to help and to overthrow.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then Amaziah said to the man of God, \u201CBut what shall  we do
        about the hundred talents which I have given to the troops of Israel?\u201DAnd
        the man of God answered, \u201CThe Lord is able to give you much more than
        this.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: So Amaziah discharged the troops that had come to him from Ephraim,
        to go back home. Therefore their anger was greatly aroused against Judah,
        and they returned home in great anger.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then Amaziah strengthened himself, and leading his people, he went
        to the Valley of Salt and killed ten thousand of the people of Seir. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Also the children of Judah took captive ten thousand alive, brought
        them to the top of the rock, and cast them down from the top of the rock,
        so that they all were dashed in pieces.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: But as for the soldiers of the army which Amaziah had discharged,
        so that they would not go with him to battle, they raided the cities of Judah
        from Samaria to Beth Horon, killed three thousand in them, and took much
        spoil.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now it was so, after Amaziah came from the slaughter of the Edomites,
        that he brought the gods of the people of Seir, set them up to  be  his gods,
        and bowed down before them and burned incense to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Therefore the anger of the Lord was aroused against Amaziah, and
        He sent him a prophet who said to him, \u201CWhy have you sought the gods
        of the people, which could not rescue their own people from your hand?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Israel Defeats Judah'
      title: Israel Defeats Judah
      number: 16
      content: "So it was, as he talked with him, that the  king said to him, \u201CHave
        we made you the king\u2019s counselor? Cease! Why should you be killed?\u201DThen
        the prophet ceased, and said, \u201CI know that God has determined to destroy
        you, because you have done this and have not heeded my advice.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Now Amaziah king of Judah asked advice and sent to Joash the son
        of Jehoahaz, the son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, \u201CCome, let us
        face one another in  battle.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And Joash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, \u201CThe
        thistle that was in Lebanon sent to the cedar that was in Lebanon, saying,
        \u2018Give your daughter to my son as wife\u2019; and a wild beast that was
        in Lebanon passed by and trampled the thistle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Indeed you say that you have defeated the Edomites, and your heart
        is lifted up to boast. Stay at home now; why should you meddle with trouble,
        that you should fall\u2014you and Judah with you?\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But Amaziah would not heed, for it came from God, that He might give
        them into the hand of  their  enemies, because they sought the gods of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So Joash king of Israel went out; and he and Amaziah king of Judah
        faced one another at Beth Shemesh, which belongs to Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Judah was defeated by Israel, and every man fled to his tent. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then Joash the king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the
        son of Joash, the son of Jehoahaz, at Beth Shemesh; and he brought him to
        Jerusalem, and broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the Gate of Ephraim
        to the Corner Gate\u2014four hundred cubits. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Death of Amaziah'
      title: Death of Amaziah
      number: 24
      content: "And he  took all the gold and silver, all the articles that were
        found in the house of God with Obed-Edom, the treasures of the king\u2019s
        house, and hostages, and returned to Samaria."
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after
        the death of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, from first to last, indeed are
        they not written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'After the time that Amaziah turned away from following the Lord,
        they made a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to Lachish;
        but they sent after him to Lachish and killed him there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: Then they brought him on horses and buried him with his fathers in
        the City of Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Uzziah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Uzziah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Now all the people of Judah took Uzziah, who was sixteen years old,
        and made him king instead of his father Amaziah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: He built Elath and restored it to Judah, after the king rested with
        his fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Uzziah was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned
        fifty-two years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jecholiah of Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he did what  was  right in the sight of the Lord, according to
        all that his father Amaziah had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: He sought God in the days of Zechariah, who had understanding in the
        visions of God; and as long as he sought the Lord, God made him prosper.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now he went out and made war against the Philistines, and broke down
        the wall of Gath, the wall of Jabneh, and the wall of Ashdod; and he built
        cities around Ashdod and among the Philistines. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'God helped him against the Philistines, against the Arabians who
        lived in Gur Baal, and against the Meunites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: Also the Ammonites brought tribute to Uzziah. His fame spread as far
        as the entrance of Egypt, for he became exceedingly strong.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at the Corner Gate, at the Valley
        Gate, and at the corner buttress of the wall; then he fortified them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: Also he built towers in the desert. He dug many wells, for he had
        much livestock, both in the lowlands and in the plains; he  also  had farmers
        and vinedressers in the mountains and in Carmel, for he loved the soil.
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Moreover Uzziah had an army of fighting men who went out to war by
        companies, according to the number on their roll as prepared by Jeiel the
        scribe and Maaseiah the officer, under the hand of Hananiah, one of the king\u2019s
        captains. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The total number of chief officers of the mighty men of valor was
        two thousand six hundred. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And under their authority was an army of three hundred and seven
        thousand five hundred, that made war with mighty power, to help the king
        against the enemy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Uzziah prepared for them, for the entire army, shields, spears,
        helmets, body armor, bows, and slings to  cast stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: "15: The Penalty for Uzziah\u2019s Pride"
      title: "The Penalty for Uzziah\u2019s Pride"
      number: 15
      content: And he made devices in Jerusalem, invented by skillful men, to be
        on the towers and the corners, to shoot arrows and large stones. So his fame
        spread far and wide, for he was marvelously helped till he became strong.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But when he was strong his heart was lifted up, to his destruction,
        for he transgressed against the Lord his God by entering the temple of the
        Lord to burn incense on the altar of incense. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So Azariah the priest went in after him, and with him were eighty
        priests of the Lord\u2014valiant men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And they withstood King Uzziah, and said to him, \u201CIt  is not
        for you, Uzziah, to burn incense to the Lord, but for the priests, the sons
        of Aaron, who are consecrated to burn incense. Get out of the sanctuary,
        for you have trespassed! You shall  have no honor from the Lord God.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then Uzziah became furious; and he had a censer in his hand to burn
        incense. And while he was angry with the priests, leprosy broke out on his
        forehead, before the priests in the house of the Lord, beside the incense
        altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And Azariah the chief priest and all the priests looked at him, and
        there, on his forehead, he was leprous; so they thrust him out of that place.
        Indeed he also hurried to get out, because the Lord had struck him.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "King Uzziah was a leper until the day of his death. He dwelt in an
        isolated house, because he was a leper; for he was cut off from the house
        of the Lord. Then Jotham his son was over the king\u2019s house, judging
        the people of the land."
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Uzziah, from first to last, the prophet
        Isaiah the son of Amoz wrote. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "So Uzziah rested with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers
        in the field of burial which belonged to the kings, for they said, \u201CHe
        is a leper.\u201D Then Jotham his son reigned in his place."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jotham Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jotham Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "Jotham was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Jerushah the daughter
        of Zadok. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, according to
        all that his father Uzziah had done (although he did not enter the temple
        of the Lord). But still the people acted corruptly.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He built the Upper Gate of the house of the Lord, and he built extensively
        on the wall of Ophel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Moreover he built cities in the mountains of Judah, and in the forests
        he built fortresses and towers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also fought with the king of the Ammonites and defeated them.
        And the people of Ammon gave him in that year one hundred talents of silver,
        ten thousand kors of wheat, and ten thousand of barley. The people of Ammon
        paid this to him in the second and third years also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: So Jotham became mighty, because he prepared his ways before the Lord
        his God.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all his wars and his ways,
        indeed they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        sixteen years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: So Jotham rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the City
        of David. Then Ahaz his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahaz Reigns in Judah'
      title: Ahaz Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Ahaz was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen
        years in Jerusalem; and he did not do what  was right in the sight of the
        Lord, as his father David had  done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel, and made molded
        images for the Baals. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He burned incense in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, and burned
        his children in the fire, according to the abominations of the nations whom
        the Lord had cast out before the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Syria and Israel Defeat Judah'
      title: Syria and Israel Defeat Judah
      number: 4
      content: And he sacrificed and burned incense on the high places, on the hills,
        and under every green tree.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore the Lord his God delivered him into the hand of the king
        of Syria. They defeated him, and carried away a great multitude of them as
        captives, and brought them to Damascus. Then he was also delivered into the
        hand of the king of Israel, who defeated him with a great slaughter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For Pekah the son of Remaliah killed one hundred and twenty thousand
        in Judah in one day, all valiant men, because they had forsaken the Lord
        God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Zichri, a mighty man of Ephraim, killed Maaseiah the king\u2019s
        son, Azrikam the officer over the house, and Elkanah who  was second to the
        king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Israel Returns the Captives'
      title: Israel Returns the Captives
      number: 8
      content: And the children of Israel carried away captive of their brethren
        two hundred thousand women, sons, and daughters; and they also took away
        much spoil from them, and brought the spoil to Samaria.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "But a prophet of the Lord was there, whose name was Oded; and he
        went out before the army that came to Samaria, and said to them: \u201CLook,
        because the Lord God of your fathers was angry with Judah, He has delivered
        them into your hand; but you have killed them in a rage that  reaches up
        to heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now you propose to force the children of Judah and Jerusalem
        to be your male and female slaves; but  are you not also guilty before the
        Lord your God? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Now hear me, therefore, and return the captives, whom you have taken
        captive from your brethren, for the fierce wrath of the Lord  is upon you.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then some of the heads of the children of Ephraim, Azariah the son
        of Johanan, Berechiah the son of Meshillemoth, Jehizkiah the son of Shallum,
        and Amasa the son of Hadlai, stood up against those who came from the war, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "and said to them, \u201CYou shall not bring the captives here, for
        we already have offended the Lord. You intend to add to our sins and to our
        guilt; for our guilt is great, and there  is fierce wrath against Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'So the armed men left the captives and the spoil before the leaders
        and all the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: Assyria Refuses to Help Judah'
      title: Assyria Refuses to Help Judah
      number: 15
      content: Then the men who were designated by name rose up and took the captives,
        and from the spoil they clothed all who were naked among them, dressed them
        and gave them sandals, gave them food and drink, and anointed them; and they
        let all the feeble ones ride on donkeys. So they brought them to their brethren
        at Jericho, the city of palm trees. Then they returned to Samaria.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'At the same time King Ahaz sent to the kings of Assyria to help him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For again the Edomites had come, attacked Judah, and carried away
        captives. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The Philistines also had invaded the cities of the lowland and of
        the South of Judah, and had taken Beth Shemesh, Aijalon, Gederoth, Sochoh
        with its villages, Timnah with its villages, and Gimzo with its villages;
        and they dwelt there. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For the Lord brought Judah low because of Ahaz king of Israel, for
        he had encouraged moral decline in Judah and had been continually unfaithful
        to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Also Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria came to him and distressed him,
        and did not assist him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: Apostasy and Death of Ahaz'
      title: Apostasy and Death of Ahaz
      number: 21
      content: For Ahaz took part of  the  treasures from the house of the Lord,
        from the house of the king, and from the leaders, and he gave it to the king
        of Assyria; but he did not help him.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now in the time of his distress King Ahaz became increasingly unfaithful
        to the Lord. This is  that King Ahaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "For he sacrificed to the gods of Damascus which had defeated him,
        saying, \u201CBecause the gods of the kings of Syria help them, I will sacrifice
        to them that they may help me.\u201D But they were the ruin of him and of
        all Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'So Ahaz gathered the articles of the house of God, cut in pieces
        the articles of the house of God, shut up the doors of the house of the Lord,
        and made for himself altars in every corner of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: And in every single city of Judah he made high places to burn incense
        to other gods, and provoked to anger the Lord God of his fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of his acts and all his ways, from first to last, indeed
        they are written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: So Ahaz rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the city,
        in Jerusalem; but they did not bring him into the tombs of the kings of Israel.
        Then Hezekiah his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Hezekiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: "Hezekiah became king when  he  was twenty-five years old, and he
        reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Abijah
        the daughter of Zechariah. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Hezekiah Cleanses the Temple'
      title: Hezekiah Cleanses the Temple
      number: 2
      content: And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, according to
        all that his father David had done.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In the first year of his reign, in the first month, he opened the
        doors of the house of the Lord and repaired them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then he brought in the priests and the Levites, and gathered them
        in the East Square, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "and said to them: \u201CHear me, Levites! Now sanctify yourselves,
        sanctify the house of the Lord God of your fathers, and carry out the rubbish
        from the holy place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For our fathers have trespassed and done evil in the eyes of the
        Lord our God; they have forsaken Him, have turned their faces away from the
        dwelling place of the Lord, and turned their backs on  Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They have also shut up the doors of the vestibule, put out the lamps,
        and have not burned incense or offered burnt offerings in the holy place
        to the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore the wrath of the Lord fell upon Judah and Jerusalem, and
        He has given them up to trouble, to desolation, and to jeering, as you see
        with your eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: For indeed, because of this our fathers have fallen by the sword;
        and our sons, our daughters, and our wives are in captivity.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CNow it  is in my heart to make a covenant with the Lord God
        of Israel, that His fierce wrath may turn away from us. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "My sons, do not be negligent now, for the Lord has chosen you to
        stand before Him, to serve Him, and that you should minister to Him and burn
        incense.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then these Levites arose: Mahath the son of Amasai and Joel the son
        of Azariah, of the sons of the Kohathites; of the sons of Merari, Kish the
        son of Abdi and Azariah the son of Jehallelel; of the Gershonites, Joah the
        son of Zimmah and Eden the son of Joah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'of the sons of Elizaphan, Shimri and Jeiel; of the sons of Asaph,
        Zechariah and Mattaniah; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: of the sons of Heman, Jehiel and Shimei; and of the sons of Jeduthun,
        Shemaiah and Uzziel.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And they gathered their brethren, sanctified themselves, and went
        according to the commandment of the king, at the words of the Lord, to cleanse
        the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Then the priests went into the inner part of the house of the Lord
        to cleanse it, and brought out all the debris that they found in the temple
        of the Lord to the court of the house of the Lord. And the Levites took it
        out and carried it to the Brook Kidron.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: Now they began to sanctify on the first day of the first month, and
        on the eighth day of the month they came to the vestibule of the Lord. So
        they sanctified the house of the Lord in eight days, and on the sixteenth
        day of the first month they finished.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then they went in to King Hezekiah and said, \u201CWe have cleansed
        all the house of the Lord, the altar of burnt offerings with all its articles,
        and the table of the showbread with all its articles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Hezekiah Restores Temple Worship'
      title: Hezekiah Restores Temple Worship
      number: 19
      content: "Moreover all the articles which King Ahaz in his reign had cast aside
        in his transgression we have prepared and sanctified; and there they are,
        before the altar of the Lord.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then King Hezekiah rose early, gathered the rulers of the city, and
        went up to the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And they brought seven bulls, seven rams, seven lambs, and seven
        male goats for a sin offering for the kingdom, for the sanctuary, and for
        Judah. Then he commanded the priests, the sons of Aaron, to offer them on
        the altar of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'So they killed the bulls, and the priests received the blood and
        sprinkled it on the altar. Likewise they killed the rams and sprinkled the
        blood on the altar. They also killed the lambs and sprinkled the blood on
        the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then they brought out the male goats for the sin offering before
        the king and the assembly, and they laid their hands on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: And the priests killed them; and they presented their blood on the
        altar as a sin offering to make an atonement for all Israel, for the king
        commanded that the burnt offering and the sin offering be  made for all Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And he stationed the Levites in the house of the Lord with cymbals,
        with stringed instruments, and with harps, according to the commandment of
        David, of Gad the king\u2019s seer, and of Nathan the prophet; for thus was
        the commandment of the Lord by His prophets. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The Levites stood with the instruments of David, and the priests
        with the trumpets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Then Hezekiah commanded them to offer the burnt offering on the altar.
        And when the burnt offering began, the song of the Lord  also began, with
        the trumpets and with the instruments of David king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So all the assembly worshiped, the singers sang, and the trumpeters
        sounded; all this  continued until the burnt offering was finished. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And when they had finished offering, the king and all who were present
        with him bowed and worshiped. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: Moreover King Hezekiah and the leaders commanded the Levites to sing
        praise to the Lord with the words of David and of Asaph the seer. So they
        sang praises with gladness, and they bowed their heads and worshiped.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Hezekiah answered and said, \u201CNow that you have consecrated
        yourselves to the Lord, come near, and bring sacrifices and thank offerings
        into the house of the Lord.\u201D So the assembly brought in sacrifices and
        thank offerings, and as many as were of a willing heart brought burnt offerings. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the number of the burnt offerings which the assembly brought
        was seventy bulls, one hundred rams, and two hundred lambs; all these were
        for a burnt offering to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The consecrated things were six hundred bulls and three thousand
        sheep. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'But the priests were too few, so that they could not skin all the
        burnt offerings; therefore their brethren the Levites helped them until the
        work was ended and until the other priests had sanctified themselves, for
        the Levites were more diligent in sanctifying themselves than the priests. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'Also the burnt offerings were in abundance, with the fat of the peace
        offerings and with  the drink offerings for every burnt offering.So the service
        of the house of the Lord was set in order. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: Then Hezekiah and all the people rejoiced that God had prepared the
        people, since the events took place so suddenly.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Keeps the Passover'
      title: Hezekiah Keeps the Passover
      number: 1
      content: 'And Hezekiah sent to all Israel and Judah, and also wrote letters
        to Ephraim and Manasseh, that they should come to the house of the Lord at
        Jerusalem, to keep the Passover to the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the king and his leaders and all the assembly in Jerusalem had
        agreed to keep the Passover in the second month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For they could not keep it at the regular time, because a sufficient
        number of priests had not consecrated themselves, nor had the people gathered
        together at Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the matter pleased the king and all the assembly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: So they resolved to make a proclamation throughout all Israel, from
        Beersheba to Dan, that they should come to keep the Passover to the Lord
        God of Israel at Jerusalem, since they had not done it for a long time in
        the prescribed manner.
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the runners went throughout all Israel and Judah with the letters
        from the king and his leaders, and spoke according to the command of the
        king: \u201CChildren of Israel, return to the Lord God of Abraham, Isaac,
        and Israel; then He will return to the remnant of you who have escaped from
        the hand of the kings of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And do not be like your fathers and your brethren, who trespassed
        against the Lord God of their fathers, so that He gave them up to desolation,
        as you see. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now do not be stiff-necked, as your fathers were, but yield yourselves
        to the Lord; and enter His sanctuary, which He has sanctified forever, and
        serve the Lord your God, that the fierceness of His wrath may turn away from
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For if you return to the Lord, your brethren and your children will 
        be  treated with compassion by those who lead them captive, so that they
        may come back to this land; for the Lord your God is  gracious and merciful,
        and will not turn His face from you if you return to Him.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So the runners passed from city to city through the country of Ephraim
        and Manasseh, as far as Zebulun; but they laughed at them and mocked them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Nevertheless some from Asher, Manasseh, and Zebulun humbled themselves
        and came to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Also the hand of God was on Judah to give them singleness of heart
        to obey the command of the king and the leaders, at the word of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Now many people, a very great assembly, gathered at Jerusalem to
        keep the Feast of Unleavened Bread in the second month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They arose and took away the altars that were in Jerusalem, and they
        took away all the incense altars and cast them into the Brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then they slaughtered the Passover lambs on the fourteenth day of
        the second month. The priests and the Levites were ashamed, and sanctified
        themselves, and brought the burnt offerings to the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They stood in their place according to their custom, according to
        the Law of Moses the man of God; the priests sprinkled the blood received
        from the hand of the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For there  were many in the assembly who had not sanctified themselves;
        therefore the Levites had charge of the slaughter of the Passover lambs for
        everyone who  was not clean, to sanctify them to the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For a multitude of the people, many from Ephraim, Manasseh, Issachar,
        and Zebulun, had not cleansed themselves, yet they ate the Passover contrary
        to what was written. But Hezekiah prayed for them, saying, \u201CMay the
        good Lord provide atonement for everyone "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "who  prepares his heart to seek God, the Lord God of his fathers,
        though he  is not cleansed according to the purification of the sanctuary.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: And the Lord listened to Hezekiah and healed the people.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So the children of Israel who were present at Jerusalem kept the
        Feast of Unleavened Bread seven days with great gladness; and the Levites
        and the priests praised the Lord day by day, singing to the Lord, accompanied
        by loud instruments. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: And Hezekiah gave encouragement to all the Levites who taught the
        good knowledge of the Lord; and they ate throughout the feast seven days,
        offering peace offerings and making confession to the Lord God of their fathers.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then the whole assembly agreed to keep the  feast  another seven
        days, and they kept it another seven days with gladness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For Hezekiah king of Judah gave to the assembly a thousand bulls
        and seven thousand sheep, and the leaders gave to the assembly a thousand
        bulls and ten thousand sheep; and a great number of priests sanctified themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The whole assembly of Judah rejoiced, also the priests and Levites,
        all the assembly that came from Israel, the sojourners who came from the
        land of Israel, and those who dwelt in Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'So there was great joy in Jerusalem, for since the time of Solomon
        the son of David, king of Israel, there  had been nothing like this in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: Then the priests, the Levites, arose and blessed the people, and their
        voice was heard; and their prayer came up to His holy dwelling place, to
        heaven.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Reforms of Hezekiah'
      title: The Reforms of Hezekiah
      number: 1
      content: "Now when all this was finished, all Israel who were present went
        out to the cities of Judah and broke the sacred pillars in pieces, cut down
        the wooden images, and threw down the high places and the altars\u2014from
        all Judah, Benjamin, Ephraim, and Manasseh\u2014until they had utterly destroyed
        them all. Then all the children of Israel returned to their own cities, every
        man to his possession."
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Hezekiah appointed the divisions of the priests and the Levites
        according to their divisions, each man according to his service, the priests
        and Levites for burnt offerings and peace offerings, to serve, to give thanks,
        and to praise in the gates of the camp of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The king also appointed a portion of his possessions for the burnt
        offerings: for the morning and evening burnt offerings, the burnt offerings
        for the Sabbaths and the New Moons and the set feasts, as it  is written
        in the Law of the Lord.'
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: Moreover he commanded the people who dwelt in Jerusalem to contribute
        support for the priests and the Levites, that they might devote themselves
        to the Law of the Lord.
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'As soon as the commandment was circulated, the children of Israel
        brought in abundance the firstfruits of grain and wine, oil and honey, and
        of all the produce of the field; and they brought in abundantly the tithe
        of everything. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And the children of Israel and Judah, who dwelt in the cities of Judah,
        brought the tithe of oxen and sheep; also the tithe of holy things which
        were consecrated to the Lord their God they laid in heaps.
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In the third month they began laying them in heaps, and they finished
        in the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And when Hezekiah and the leaders came and saw the heaps, they blessed
        the Lord and His people Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then Hezekiah questioned the priests and the Levites concerning the
        heaps. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And Azariah the chief priest, from the house of Zadok, answered him
        and said, \u201CSince the  people began to bring the offerings into the house
        of the Lord, we have had enough to eat and have plenty left, for the Lord
        has blessed His people; and what is left is this great abundance.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now Hezekiah commanded them to prepare rooms in the house of the
        Lord, and they prepared them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Then they faithfully brought in the offerings, the tithes, and the
        dedicated things; Cononiah the Levite had charge of them, and Shimei his
        brother was the next. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Jehiel, Azaziah, Nahath, Asahel, Jerimoth, Jozabad, Eliel, Ismachiah,
        Mahath, and Benaiah were overseers under the hand of Cononiah and Shimei
        his brother, at the commandment of Hezekiah the king and Azariah the ruler
        of the house of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, the keeper of the East Gate, was
        over the freewill offerings to God, to distribute the offerings of the Lord
        and the most holy things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: And under him were  Eden, Miniamin, Jeshua, Shemaiah, Amariah, and
        Shecaniah, his faithful assistants in the cities of the priests, to distribute
        allotments to their brethren by divisions, to the great as well as the small.
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Besides those males from three years old and up who were written
        in the genealogy, they distributed to everyone who entered the house of the
        Lord his daily portion for the work of his service, by his division, '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and to the priests who were written in the genealogy according to
        their father\u2019s house, and to the Levites from twenty years old and up
        according to their work, by their divisions, "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "and to all who were written in the genealogy\u2014their little ones
        and their wives, their sons and daughters, the whole company of them\u2014for
        in their faithfulness they sanctified themselves in holiness."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: Also for the sons of Aaron the priests, who  were in the fields of
        the common-lands of their cities, in every single city, there  were men who
        were designated by name to distribute portions to all the males among the
        priests and to all who were listed by genealogies among the Levites.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Thus Hezekiah did throughout all Judah, and he did what was good
        and right and true before the Lord his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And in every work that he began in the service of the house of God,
        in the law and in the commandment, to seek his God, he did it with all his
        heart. So he prospered.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sennacherib Boasts Against the Lord'
      title: Sennacherib Boasts Against the Lord
      number: 1
      content: 'After these deeds of faithfulness, Sennacherib king of Assyria came
        and entered Judah; he encamped against the fortified cities, thinking to
        win them over to himself. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And when Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib had come, and that his purpose
        was to make war against Jerusalem, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'he consulted with his leaders and commanders to stop the water from
        the springs which were outside the city; and they helped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Thus many people gathered together who stopped all the springs and
        the brook that ran through the land, saying, \u201CWhy should the kings of
        Assyria come and find much water?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he strengthened himself, built up all the wall that was broken,
        raised it up to the towers, and built another wall outside; also he repaired
        the Millo in the City of David, and made weapons and shields in abundance. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he set military captains over the people, gathered them together
        to him in the open square of the city gate, and gave them encouragement,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBe strong and courageous; do not be afraid nor dismayed before
        the king of Assyria, nor before all the multitude that is with him; for there 
        are more with us than with him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "With him is an arm of flesh; but with us is the Lord our God, to
        help us and to fight our battles.\u201D And the people were strengthened
        by the words of Hezekiah king of Judah."
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'After this Sennacherib king of Assyria sent his servants to Jerusalem
        (but he and all the forces with him laid  siege against Lachish), to Hezekiah
        king of Judah, and to all Judah who were in Jerusalem, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThus says Sennacherib king of Assyria: \u2018In what do you
        trust, that you remain under siege in Jerusalem? "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Does not Hezekiah persuade you to give yourselves over to die by
        famine and by thirst, saying, \u201CThe Lord our God will deliver us from
        the hand of the king of Assyria\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Has not the same Hezekiah taken away His high places and His altars,
        and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, saying, \u201CYou shall worship before
        one altar and burn incense on it\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Do you not know what I and my fathers have done to all the peoples
        of other lands? Were the gods of the nations of those lands in any way able
        to deliver their lands out of my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Who was  there among all the gods of those nations that my fathers
        utterly destroyed that could deliver his people from my hand, that your God
        should be able to deliver you from my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now therefore, do not let Hezekiah deceive you or persuade you like
        this, and do not believe him; for no god of any nation or kingdom was able
        to deliver his people from my hand or the hand of my fathers. How much less
        will your God deliver you from my hand?\u2019 \u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Furthermore, his servants spoke against the Lord God and against His
        servant Hezekiah.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He also wrote letters to revile the Lord God of Israel, and to speak
        against Him, saying, \u201CAs the gods of the nations of other lands have
        not delivered their people from my hand, so the God of Hezekiah will not
        deliver His people from my hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then they called out with a loud voice in Hebrew to the people of
        Jerusalem who were on the wall, to frighten them and trouble them, that they
        might take the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      title: "Sennacherib\u2019s Defeat and Death"
      number: 19
      content: "And they spoke against the God of Jerusalem, as against the gods
        of the people of the earth\u2014the work of men\u2019s hands."
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now because of this King Hezekiah and the prophet Isaiah, the son
        of Amoz, prayed and cried out to heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Then the Lord sent an angel who cut down every mighty man of valor,
        leader, and captain in the camp of the king of Assyria. So he returned shamefaced
        to his own land. And when he had gone into the temple of his god, some of
        his own offspring struck him down with the sword there.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Thus the Lord saved Hezekiah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem from
        the hand of Sennacherib the king of Assyria, and from the hand of all others,
        and guided them on every side. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Hezekiah Humbles Himself'
      title: Hezekiah Humbles Himself
      number: 23
      content: And many brought gifts to the Lord at Jerusalem, and presents to Hezekiah
        king of Judah, so that he was exalted in the sight of all nations thereafter.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'In those days Hezekiah was sick and near death, and he prayed to
        the Lord; and He spoke to him and gave him a sign. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'But Hezekiah did not repay according to the favor shown him, for
        his heart was lifted up; therefore wrath was looming over him and over Judah
        and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: "26: Hezekiah\u2019s Wealth and Honor"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Wealth and Honor"
      number: 26
      content: Then Hezekiah humbled himself for the pride of his heart, he and the
        inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that the wrath of the Lord did not come upon
        them in the days of Hezekiah.
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Hezekiah had very great riches and honor. And he made himself treasuries
        for silver, for gold, for precious stones, for spices, for shields, and for
        all kinds of desirable items; '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'storehouses for the harvest of grain, wine, and oil; and stalls for
        all kinds of livestock, and folds for flocks. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Moreover he provided cities for himself, and possessions of flocks
        and herds in abundance; for God had given him very much property. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: This same Hezekiah also stopped the water outlet of Upper Gihon, and
        brought the water by tunnel to the west side of the City of David. Hezekiah
        prospered in all his works.
      comments: []
    - name: '31: Death of Hezekiah'
      title: Death of Hezekiah
      number: 31
      content: However, regarding the ambassadors of the princes of Babylon, whom
        they sent to him to inquire about the wonder that was done in the land, God
        withdrew from him, in order to test him, that He might know all that  was
        in his heart.
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah, and his goodness, indeed they
        are written in the vision of Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, and in
        the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: So Hezekiah rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the upper
        tombs of the sons of David; and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem
        honored him at his death. Then Manasseh his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Manasseh Reigns in Judah'
      title: Manasseh Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned
        fifty-five years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to the abominations
        of the nations whom the Lord had cast out before the children of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For he rebuilt the high places which Hezekiah his father had broken
        down; he raised up altars for the Baals, and made wooden images; and he worshiped
        all the host of heaven and served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He also built altars in the house of the Lord, of which the Lord
        had said, \u201CIn Jerusalem shall My name be forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts
        of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Also he caused his sons to pass through the fire in the Valley of
        the Son of Hinnom; he practiced soothsaying, used witchcraft and sorcery,
        and consulted mediums and spiritists. He did much evil in the sight of the
        Lord, to provoke Him to anger. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He even set a carved image, the idol which he had made, in the house
        of God, of which God had said to David and to Solomon his son, \u201CIn this
        house and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel,
        I will put My name forever; "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "and I will not again remove the foot of Israel from the land which
        I have appointed for your fathers\u2014only if they are careful to do all
        that I have commanded them, according to the whole law and the statutes and
        the ordinances by the hand of Moses.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: Manasseh Restored After Repentance'
      title: Manasseh Restored After Repentance
      number: 9
      content: So Manasseh seduced Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to do more
        evil than the nations whom the Lord had destroyed before the children of
        Israel.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And the Lord spoke to Manasseh and his people, but they would not
        listen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore the Lord brought upon them the captains of the army of
        the king of Assyria, who took Manasseh with hooks, bound him with bronze
        fetters, and carried him off to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when he was in affliction, he implored the Lord his God, and
        humbled himself greatly before the God of his fathers, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: and prayed to Him; and He received his entreaty, heard his supplication,
        and brought him back to Jerusalem into his kingdom. Then Manasseh knew that
        the Lord  was God.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'After this he built a wall outside the City of David on the west
        side of Gihon, in the valley, as far as the entrance of the Fish Gate; and
        it  enclosed Ophel, and he raised it to a very great height. Then he put
        military captains in all the fortified cities of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He took away the foreign gods and the idol from the house of the
        Lord, and all the altars that he had built in the mount of the house of the
        Lord and in Jerusalem; and he cast them out of the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He also repaired the altar of the Lord, sacrificed peace offerings
        and thank offerings on it, and commanded Judah to serve the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: Death of Manasseh'
      title: Death of Manasseh
      number: 17
      content: Nevertheless the people still sacrificed on the high places, but only
        to the Lord their God.
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh, his prayer to his God, and
        the words of the seers who spoke to him in the name of the Lord God of Israel,
        indeed they are  written in the book of the kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Also his prayer and how  God received his entreaty, and all his sin
        and trespass, and the sites where he built high places and set up wooden
        images and carved images, before he was humbled, indeed they are written
        among the sayings of Hozai. '
      comments: []
    - name: "20: Amon\u2019s Reign and Death"
      title: "Amon\u2019s Reign and Death"
      number: 20
      content: So Manasseh rested with his fathers, and they buried him in his own
        house. Then his son Amon reigned in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned
        two years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But he did evil in the sight of the Lord, as his father Manasseh
        had done; for Amon sacrificed to all the carved images which his father Manasseh
        had made, and served them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: And he did not humble himself before the Lord, as his father Manasseh
        had humbled himself; but Amon trespassed more and more.
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Then his servants conspired against him, and killed him in his own
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: But the people of the land executed all those who had conspired against
        King Amon. Then the people of the land made his son Josiah king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Josiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: 'Josiah was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned thirty-one
        years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: And he did what  was right in the sight of the Lord, and walked in
        the ways of his father David; he did not turn aside to the right hand or
        to the left.
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For in the eighth year of his reign, while he was still young, he
        began to seek the God of his father David; and in the twelfth year he began
        to purge Judah and Jerusalem of the high places, the wooden images, the carved
        images, and the molded images. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They broke down the altars of the Baals in his presence, and the
        incense altars which were above them he cut down; and the wooden images,
        the carved images, and the molded images he broke in pieces, and made dust
        of them and scattered it on the graves of those who had sacrificed to them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also burned the bones of the priests on their altars, and cleansed
        Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And so  he  did in the cities of Manasseh, Ephraim, and Simeon, as
        far as Naphtali and all around, with axes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Hilkiah Finds the Book of the Law'
      title: Hilkiah Finds the Book of the Law
      number: 7
      content: When he had broken down the altars and the wooden images, had beaten
        the carved images into powder, and cut down all the incense altars throughout
        all the land of Israel, he returned to Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the eighteenth year of his reign, when he had purged the land
        and the temple, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, Maaseiah the governor
        of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz the recorder, to repair the house
        of the Lord his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'When they came to Hilkiah the high priest, they delivered the money
        that was brought into the house of God, which the Levites who kept the doors
        had gathered from the hand of Manasseh and Ephraim, from all the remnant
        of Israel, from all Judah and Benjamin, and which they had brought back to
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then they put it in the hand of the foremen who had the oversight
        of the house of the Lord; and they gave it to the workmen who worked in the
        house of the Lord, to repair and restore the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They gave it to the craftsmen and builders to buy hewn stone and
        timber for beams, and to floor the houses which the kings of Judah had destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the men did the work faithfully. Their overseers were Jahath
        and Obadiah the Levites, of the sons of Merari, and Zechariah and Meshullam,
        of the sons of the Kohathites, to supervise. Others  of the Levites, all
        of whom were skillful with instruments of music, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: were  over the burden bearers and were overseers of all who did work
        in any kind of service. And some of the Levites were scribes, officers, and
        gatekeepers.
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now when they brought out the money that was brought into the house
        of the Lord, Hilkiah the priest found the Book of the Law of the Lord  given
        by Moses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then Hilkiah answered and said to Shaphan the scribe, \u201CI have
        found the Book of the Law in the house of the Lord.\u201D And Hilkiah gave
        the book to Shaphan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "So Shaphan carried the book to the king, bringing the king word,
        saying, \u201CAll that was committed to your servants they are doing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And they have gathered the money that was found in the house of the
        Lord, and have delivered it into the hand of the overseers and the workmen.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Shaphan the scribe told the king, saying, \u201CHilkiah the
        priest has given me a book.\u201D And Shaphan read it before the king."
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Thus it happened, when the king heard the words of the Law, that
        he tore his clothes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah, Ahikam the son of Shaphan, Abdon
        the son of Micah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah a servant of the king, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CGo, inquire of the Lord for me, and for those who are left
        in Israel and Judah, concerning the words of the book that is found; for
        great is the wrath of the Lord that is poured out on us, because our fathers
        have not kept the word of the Lord, to do according to all that is written
        in this book.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: So Hilkiah and those the king had  appointed went to Huldah the prophetess,
        the wife of Shallum the son of Tokhath, the son of Hasrah, keeper of the
        wardrobe. (She dwelt in Jerusalem in the Second Quarter.) And they spoke
        to her to that effect.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then she answered them, \u201CThus says the Lord God of Israel, \u2018Tell
        the man who sent you to Me, "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CThus says the Lord: \u2018Behold, I will bring calamity on
        this place and on its inhabitants, all the curses that are written in the
        book which they have read before the king of Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "because they have forsaken Me and burned incense to other gods, that
        they might provoke Me to anger with all the works of their hands. Therefore
        My wrath will be poured out on this place, and not be quenched.\u2019 \u201D
        \u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "But as for the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the Lord,
        in this manner you shall speak to him, \u2018Thus says the Lord God of Israel:
        \u201CConcerning the words which you have heard\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "because your heart was tender, and you humbled yourself before God
        when you heard His words against this place and against its inhabitants,
        and you humbled yourself before Me, and you tore your clothes and wept before
        Me, I also have heard you,\u201D says the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Josiah Restores True Worship'
      title: Josiah Restores True Worship
      number: 28
      content: "\u201CSurely I will gather you to your fathers, and you shall be
        gathered to your grave in peace; and your eyes shall not see all the calamity
        which I will bring on this place and its inhabitants.\u201D \u2019 \u201D
        So they brought back word to the king."
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Then the king sent and gathered all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "The king went up to the house of the Lord, with all the men of Judah
        and the inhabitants of Jerusalem\u2014the priests and the Levites, and all
        the people, great and small. And he read in their hearing all the words of
        the Book of the Covenant which had been found in the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Then the king stood in his place and made a covenant before the Lord,
        to follow the Lord, and to keep His commandments and His testimonies and
        His statutes with all his heart and all his soul, to perform the words of
        the covenant that were written in this book. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And he made all who were present in Jerusalem and Benjamin take a
        stand. So the inhabitants of Jerusalem did according to the covenant of God,
        the God of their fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: Thus Josiah removed all the abominations from all the country that
        belonged to the children of Israel, and made all who were present in Israel
        diligently serve the Lord their God. All his days they did not depart from
        following the Lord God of their fathers.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Josiah Keeps the Passover'
      title: Josiah Keeps the Passover
      number: 1
      content: 'Now Josiah kept a Passover to the Lord in Jerusalem, and they slaughtered
        the Passover lambs on the fourteenth day of the first month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And he set the priests in their duties and encouraged them for the
        service of the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then he said to the Levites who taught all Israel, who were holy
        to the Lord: \u201CPut the holy ark in the house which Solomon the son of
        David, king of Israel, built. It  shall no longer be a burden on your shoulders.
        Now serve the Lord your God and His people Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Prepare yourselves  according to your fathers\u2019 houses, according
        to your divisions, following the written instruction of David king of Israel
        and the written instruction of Solomon his son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And stand in the holy place according to the divisions of the fathers\u2019
        houses of your brethren the lay people, and according  to the division of
        the father\u2019s house of the Levites. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So slaughter the Passover offerings,  consecrate yourselves, and
        prepare them for your brethren, that they may do according to the word of
        the Lord by the hand of Moses.\u201D"
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then Josiah gave the lay people lambs and young goats from the flock,
        all for Passover offerings for all who were present, to the number of thirty
        thousand, as well as three thousand cattle; these were from the king\u2019s
        possessions. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And his leaders gave willingly to the people, to the priests, and
        to the Levites. Hilkiah, Zechariah, and Jehiel, rulers of the house of God,
        gave to the priests for the Passover offerings two thousand six hundred from 
        the  flock, and three hundred cattle. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Also Conaniah, his brothers Shemaiah and Nethanel, and Hashabiah and
        Jeiel and Jozabad, chief of the Levites, gave to the Levites for Passover
        offerings five thousand from  the  flock and five hundred cattle.
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So the service was prepared, and the priests stood in their places,
        and the Levites in their divisions, according to the king\u2019s command. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And they slaughtered the Passover offerings; and the priests sprinkled
        the  blood with their hands, while the Levites skinned the  animals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then they removed the burnt offerings that they might give them to
        the divisions of the fathers\u2019 houses of the lay people, to offer to
        the Lord, as it  is written in the Book of Moses. And so they  did with the
        cattle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Also they roasted the Passover offerings with fire according to the
        ordinance; but the other holy offerings they boiled in pots, in caldrons,
        and in pans, and divided them quickly among all the lay people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then afterward they prepared portions for themselves and for the
        priests, because the priests, the sons of Aaron, were  busy in offering burnt
        offerings and fat until night; therefore the Levites prepared portions for
        themselves and for the priests, the sons of Aaron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the singers, the sons of Asaph, were in their places, according
        to the command of David, Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun the king\u2019s seer.
        Also the gatekeepers were at each gate; they did not have to leave their
        position, because their brethren the Levites prepared portions for them."
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So all the service of the Lord was prepared the same day, to keep
        the Passover and to offer burnt offerings on the altar of the Lord, according
        to the command of King Josiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the children of Israel who were present kept the Passover at
        that time, and the Feast of Unleavened Bread for seven days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There had been no Passover kept in Israel like that since the days
        of Samuel the prophet; and none of the kings of Israel had kept such a Passover
        as Josiah kept, with the priests and the Levites, all Judah and Israel who
        were present, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: Josiah Dies in Battle'
      title: Josiah Dies in Battle
      number: 19
      content: In the eighteenth year of the reign of Josiah this Passover was kept.
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'After all this, when Josiah had prepared the temple, Necho king of
        Egypt came up to fight against Carchemish by the Euphrates; and Josiah went
        out against him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But he sent messengers to him, saying, \u201CWhat have I to do with
        you, king of Judah? I  have not come against you this day, but against the
        house with which I have war; for God commanded me to make haste. Refrain
        from  meddling  with God, who is with me, lest He destroy you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Nevertheless Josiah would not turn his face from him, but disguised
        himself so that he might fight with him, and did not heed the words of Necho
        from the mouth of God. So he came to fight in the Valley of Megiddo.
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the archers shot King Josiah; and the king said to his servants,
        \u201CTake me away, for I am severely wounded.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: His servants therefore took him out of that chariot and put him in
        the second chariot that he had, and they brought him to Jerusalem. So he
        died, and was buried in one  of the tombs of his fathers. And all Judah and
        Jerusalem mourned for Josiah.
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Jeremiah also lamented for Josiah. And to this day all the singing
        men and the singing women speak of Josiah in their lamentations. They made
        it a custom in Israel; and indeed they are written in the Laments.
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah and his goodness, according to
        what  was written in the Law of the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: and his deeds from first to last, indeed they are written in the book
        of the kings of Israel and Judah.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoahaz'
      title: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoahaz
      number: 1
      content: "Then the people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, and
        made him king in his father\u2019s place in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned
        three months in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the king of Egypt deposed him at Jerusalem; and he imposed on
        the land a tribute of one hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoiakim'
      title: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoiakim
      number: 4
      content: "Then the king of Egypt made Jehoahaz\u2019s brother Eliakim king
        over Judah and Jerusalem, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. And Necho took
        Jehoahaz his brother and carried him off to Egypt."
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. And he did evil in the sight of the Lord his God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against him, and bound him
        in bronze fetters to carry him off to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Nebuchadnezzar also carried off some of the articles from the house
        of the Lord to Babylon, and put them in his temple at Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoiachin'
      title: The Reign and Captivity of Jehoiachin
      number: 8
      content: Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, the abominations which he did,
        and what was found against him, indeed they are written in the book of the
        kings of Israel and Judah. Then Jehoiachin his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Jehoiachin was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned
        in Jerusalem three months and ten days. And he did evil in the sight of the
        Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Zedekiah Reigns in Judah'
      title: Zedekiah Reigns in Judah
      number: 10
      content: "At the turn of the year King Nebuchadnezzar summoned him and took
        him to Babylon, with the costly articles from the house of the Lord, and
        made Zedekiah, Jehoiakim\u2019s brother, king over Judah and Jerusalem."
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned
        eleven years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord his God, and  did not humble
        himself before Jeremiah the prophet, who  spoke from the mouth of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And he also rebelled against King Nebuchadnezzar, who had made him
        swear an  oath by God; but he stiffened his neck and hardened his heart against
        turning to the Lord God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: The Fall of Jerusalem'
      title: The Fall of Jerusalem
      number: 14
      content: Moreover all the leaders of the priests and the people transgressed
        more and more, according to all the abominations of the nations, and defiled
        the house of the Lord which He had consecrated in Jerusalem.
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Lord God of their fathers sent warnings to them by His messengers,
        rising up early and sending them, because He had compassion on His people
        and on His dwelling place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: But they mocked the messengers of God, despised His words, and scoffed
        at His prophets, until the wrath of the Lord arose against His people, till
        there  was no remedy.
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore He brought against them the king of the Chaldeans, who
        killed their young men with the sword in the house of their sanctuary, and
        had no compassion on young man or virgin, on the aged or the weak; He gave
        them all into his hand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And all the articles from the house of God, great and small, the
        treasures of the house of the Lord, and the treasures of the king and of
        his leaders, all these he took to Babylon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Then they burned the house of God, broke down the wall of Jerusalem,
        burned all its palaces with fire, and destroyed all its precious possessions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And those who escaped from the sword he carried away to Babylon,
        where they became servants to him and his sons until the rule of the kingdom
        of Persia, '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Proclamation of Cyrus'
      title: The Proclamation of Cyrus
      number: 21
      content: to fulfill the word of the Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah, until the
        land had enjoyed her Sabbaths. As long as she lay desolate she kept Sabbath,
        to fulfill seventy years.
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, that the word of the
        Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah might be fulfilled, the Lord stirred up the
        spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, so that he made a proclamation throughout
        all his kingdom, and also put  it in writing, saying,
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Thus says Cyrus king of Persia:All the kingdoms of the earth the Lord
        God of heaven has given me. And He has commanded me to build Him a house
        at Jerusalem which is in Judah. Who is among you of all His people? May the
        Lord his God be with him, and let him go up!
      comments: []
